INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-1', 'Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-2', 'Even if one of its arms is eaten, it''s fine. The Pokémon regenerates quickly and will go right back to normal.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-3', 'The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-4', 'The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. Starly try to peck it off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-5', 'Using its tentacles to lash itself to trees, it lies in wait for prey, luring it close with sweet-smelling drool.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-6', 'They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-7', 'They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-8', 'They raise their heads to intimidate opponents but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-9', 'Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-10', 'Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-11', 'Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-12', 'Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-13', 'When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-14', 'When its boulder is broken in battles for territory, it feels unsure and begins to weaken.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-15', 'Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-16', 'This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-17', 'The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-18', 'In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-19', 'It is said that Charizard''s fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-20', 'As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-21', 'Each of its nine tails is imbued with supernatural power, and it can live for a thousand years.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-22', 'One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-23', 'This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-25', 'It can deftly dodge its foe''s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-26', 'When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When it trouble, it emits smoke.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-27', 'It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-28', 'This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-30', 'A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-31', 'Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-32', 'A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-33', 'A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-34', 'Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-35', 'If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-36', 'It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-37', 'The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-38', 'Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-39', 'Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-40', 'By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-41', 'It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-42', 'It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-43', 'It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-46', 'A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-47', 'It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-48', 'It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-49', 'They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-50', 'The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-51', 'This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-53', 'A Pokémon created by recombining Mew''s genes. It''s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-55', 'It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-56', 'This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun''s movement all day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-57', 'A Pokémon that startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-59', 'If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-60', 'If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-61', 'It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-62', 'Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-63', 'The croaking that Toxicroak produces before a battle is for churning the poison it has stored in its poison sac.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-64', 'The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-65', 'It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-66', 'The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-67', 'Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-68', 'It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-69', 'Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-70', 'It stares intently at everything. It can become so obsessed with watching that it doesn''t notice attacks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-71', 'They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-72', 'Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-73', 'They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-74', 'Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-75', 'Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-76', 'When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-78', 'The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-79', 'It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-80', 'A well-trained one can sense auras to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-81', 'When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-83', 'It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-84', 'Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-85', 'Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-86', 'The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-87', 'Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-89', 'It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-90', 'Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-91', 'It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-92', 'On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-93', 'It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-94', 'It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-95', 'It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-96', 'It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-97', 'It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-98', 'After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-99', 'This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-103', 'For some reason, it likes to land on people''s heads softly and act like it''s a hat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-104', 'These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-105', 'Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-106', 'It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-107', 'Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-108', 'The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-114', 'This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-115', 'This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC1', 'Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC2', 'When it gets dirty, its leaves can''t be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC3', 'It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior''s noble eyes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC4', 'Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC5', 'A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC6', 'A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC7', 'It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC8', 'If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC9', 'If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC10', 'To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC12', 'When its opponent can''t be paralyzed, it contorts itself with unexpected speed and flops away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC13', 'Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC14', 'Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC15', 'It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC16', 'In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC17', 'Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC18', 'Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC19', 'Cinccino''s body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC22', 'This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw11-RC23', 'It glides on its outstretched membrane while shocking foes with the electricity stored in the pouches on its cheeks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-1', 'This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-2', 'Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-3', 'Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-4', 'This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-5', 'It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-6', 'Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-7', 'Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-8', 'It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-9', 'They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days, their bodies are heavier, so they take shelter beneath big trees.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-10', 'When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-11', 'Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-12', 'Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-13', 'The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-14', 'Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-15', 'The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon''s fur. People use it to mark the seasons.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-16', 'The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-17', 'This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-18', 'This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600º F.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-19', 'A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-20', 'When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-21', 'Its internal fire burns at 2,500º F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-22', 'It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-23', 'The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-24', 'Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they''ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-25', 'Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other''s school.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-26', 'When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-27', 'It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-28', 'When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-29', 'Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-30', 'It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-31', 'It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-32', 'The energy made in its cheeks'' electric pouches is stored inside its membranes and released while it is gliding.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-33', 'Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-34', 'When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-35', 'The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-36', 'Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-37', 'Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-38', 'It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-39', 'It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-40', 'With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-41', 'The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-42', 'They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-43', 'Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-44', 'They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-45', 'They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-46', 'Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-47', 'Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-48', 'They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers'' life spans.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-49', 'Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-50', 'They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-51', 'When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-52', 'Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-53', 'The solar energy absorbed by its body''s orange crystals is magnified internally and fired from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('bw2-54', 'It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.')
