INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-7', 'Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-8', 'The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-9', 'It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-10', 'It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-11', 'It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-12', 'It looks like a fluffy cloud when it is in flight. It hums with its soprano voice.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-13', 'Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-14', 'It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-15', 'An ancient clay figurine that came to life as a Pokémon from exposure to a mysterious ray of light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-16', 'It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-17', 'Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-18', 'Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-19', 'Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even if someone just woke up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-20', 'The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-21', 'It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokémon on its back. It understands human speech.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-22', 'Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-23', 'A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-24', 'Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-25', 'When people bicker, it is said to arise from the depths of lakes to becalm violent hearts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-26', 'It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-27', 'It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-28', 'Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-29', 'Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-30', 'The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-31', 'It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-32', 'Its fine fur feels sublime to the touch. It can expand its body by inhaling air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-33', 'The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-34', 'It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day''s desert heat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-35', 'Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-36', 'It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-37', 'It floats using its well-developed floatation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-38', 'It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-39', 'It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-40', 'It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-41', 'It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-42', 'It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-43', 'It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-44', 'The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-45', 'Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-46', 'Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-47', 'A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-48', 'It dips its large bill in the sea, then scoops up numerous prey along with water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-49', 'With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-50', 'It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon''s nest and claims it as its own.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-51', 'A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-52', 'For many generations, it has feuded with ZANGOOSE. It whets its bladed tail on rocks for battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-53', 'Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-54', 'Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the SHELLDER on its tail bites down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-55', 'It is said to appear in front of kindly people to scatter a glowing down called "joy dust."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-56', 'Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-57', 'Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-58', 'On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-59', 'It has feuded with SEVIPER for many generations. Its sharp claws are its biggest weapons.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-60', 'It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-61', 'It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-62', 'By storing water in its body, this desert dweller can survive 30 days without water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-63', 'It releases a stench from its red antenna to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-64', 'It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-65', 'It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-66', 'It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-67', 'It is famous for its shabby appearance. While populous, they tend to cluster in set locations.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-68', 'It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-69', 'It conveys its feelings using different cries. It works in a pack to cleverly take down prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-70', 'It has a soft and bouncy body. Once it starts bouncing, it becomes impossible to stop.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-71', 'With its sweet aroma, it guides VOLBEAT to draw signs with light in the night sky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-72', 'When it wavers its big, round eyes, it begins singing a lullaby that makes everyone drowsy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-73', 'While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-74', 'Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-75', 'It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-76', 'Because it turns active on nights of the full moon, it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-77', 'It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-78', 'It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-79', 'It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-80', 'To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-81', 'The world''s first artificially created Pokémon. It can travel through electronic space.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('dp4-82', 'Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.')
