INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('fut20-4', 'A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon''s body. Once that happens, it''s ready to fight at full power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('fut20-5', 'When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won''t be able to resist weeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-3', 'For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antennae on its head to drive away enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-4', 'A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-5', 'It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-6', 'Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-7', 'The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-8', 'It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-9', 'It swings its long antlers wildly to attack. During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-15', 'Very competitive, this Pokémon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-16', 'Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather''s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-19', 'Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-20', 'Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-21', 'If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-22', 'In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-23', 'Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-25', 'A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-26', 'It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-27', 'When its electricity builds, its muscles are stimulated, and it becomes more aggressive than usual.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-29', 'A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-30', 'Even though it has no eyes, it can sense obstacles using ultrasonic waves it emits from it mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-31', 'Once it bites, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-32', 'It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-33', 'Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-34', 'It licks with its gaseous tongue to steal the victim''s life force. It lurks in darkness for prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-35', 'Hiding in people''s shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-36', 'It wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-38', 'Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-39', 'In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-40', 'It hefts a Graveler repeatedly to strengthen its entire body. It uses every type of martial arts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-41', 'Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-42', 'Its four ruggedly developed arms can launch a flurry of 1,000 punches in just two seconds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-43', 'Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-44', 'With a free and uncaring nature, it doesn''t mind if pieces break off while it rolls down mountains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-45', 'It tumbles down mountains, leaving grooves from peak to base. Stay clear of these grooves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-47', 'The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-48', 'The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-49', 'It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-50', 'It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-51', 'Its hearing is so acute it can hear a pin drop over half a mile away. It lives on quiet mountains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-52', 'It is adept at conning people. It is said to be able to create walls out of thin air by miming.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-53', 'Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-54', 'Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks in an instant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-55', 'The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-56', 'An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-57', 'After heightening its will to fight by whipping itself with its three tails, it charges at full speed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-58', 'It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC1', 'Running around, climbing trees, playing hide-and-seek! Another wonderful day begins!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC2', 'I wonder if I would look a little cuter with a beautiful flower?')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC3', 'My Charmander is so rambunctious! I wonder if we can become good friends?')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC4', 'My precious friend who is always with me. I have so many things I want to tell you.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC5', 'No matter what happens, if we stick together, we can get past it. Forever and ever.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC7', 'What a delicious-looking snowman! I think I''ll sneak a bite. It''s OK…no one''s looking, right?')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC8', 'Spring is already here, so goodbye…')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC9', 'The plan for today is to do nothing. My awesome tail is all curled up, and my ears are tired, too.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC10', 'Crackle…buzz…Dedenne…?! Beep…')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC11', 'When she''s surrounded by cushions and dressers that I like, she looks just like a princess!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC12', 'When Mom gets in the kitchen, the happiest things happen. I can feel my mouth watering!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC13', 'The twinkle of the stars. The destiny of love. A miracle that grants wishes in the night sky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC14', 'My number one. Exceptionally cute. A little princess.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC15', 'Intense silence. Two lamplights. Keep waiting for night to end.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC16', 'Hidden away in its jet-black wings is a red passion.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC17', 'It''s OK. No one will take away your flower. You look cute even when you''re angry.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC18', 'The five of us team up to be the Pretty Young Girl Force! We''ll show you some beautiful moves!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC19', 'My fluffy heart makes me feel like a marshmallow. A thrilling macaron full of colorful magic. Everybody''s crazy about the taste of candy! ☆')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC20', 'The cakes Slurpuff makes always look just like that one Pokémon it likes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC22', 'Open the magic door and a dream-colored party will start again today. I''ll teach you the secret password.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC23', 'Wings and beaks. I like yours, and I like mine, too.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC24', 'This fluffiness makes everyone go crazy. Is it really that charming?')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC25', 'Little friends, thanks for always helping me look so cute!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('g1-RC29', 'A yellow body is proof of good health. If you touch its bright-red cheeks, you''ll see its shining, smiling face!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-1', 'This legendary Chinese Pokémon is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-2', 'When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-3', 'With its acute hearing, it can pick up sounds from far away. It usually hides in quiet places.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-4', 'Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-5', 'It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-6', 'Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores—it can even float around the world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-7', 'Its nine beautiful tails are filled with a wondrous energy that could keep it alive for 1,000 years.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-8', 'Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-9', 'Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on boulders and boat hulls as it swims.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-10', 'If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-11', 'The berries it stores in its vase-like shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-12', 'It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-13', 'It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to build up its counterstrike.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-14', 'The tail''s tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-15', 'It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It''s hard to tell which end is which.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-16', 'Water-repellent powder on its wings enables it to collect honey, even in the heaviest of rains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-17', 'Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-18', 'If a head drops off, it emits a telepathic call in search of others to form an Exeggcute cluster.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-19', 'If it eats the plant stalk it carries as emergency rations, it runs off in search of a new stalk.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-20', 'When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-21', 'It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-22', 'Because its fangs are too heavy, it always keeps its head tilted down. However, its bite is powerful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-23', 'Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-24', 'They have gentle hearts. Because they rarely fight, many have been caught. Their number has dwindled.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-25', 'The spot patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-26', 'Meganium''s breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-27', 'Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks in an instant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-28', 'Despite its small size, it can zap even adult humans. However, if it does so, it also surprises itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-29', 'If it digs at an incredible pace, it may snap off its spike and claws. They grow back in a day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-30', 'Its lips are the most sensitive part of its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-31', 'It converts sunlight into energy. In the darkness after sunset, it closes its petals and becomes still.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-32', 'It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-33', 'Even though it is small, it can''t be ignored because it will slug any handy target without warning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-34', 'If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-35', 'A spicy aroma emanates from around its neck. The aroma acts as a stimulant to restore health.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-36', 'Anyone who takes even one taste of Blissey''s egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-37', 'It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure because of its beauty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-38', 'If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-39', 'It nests at the edge of sharp cliffs. It spends all day carrying food to its awaiting chicks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-40', 'It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its tackle is strong enough to knock down a house.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-41', 'When spotted, this Pokémon escapes backward by furiously boring into the ground with its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-42', 'As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won''t grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-43', 'This powerful Pokémon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies'' bellies, then lifts and throws them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-44', 'Its extremely flexible and elastic body makes it bounce continuously—anytime, anywhere.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-45', 'As it majestically swims, it doesn''t care if Remoraid attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-46', 'It prepares for evolution by hardening its shell as much as possible to protect its soft body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-47', 'If it is around babies, the milk it produces contains much more nutrition than usual.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-48', 'The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-49', 'This Pokémon is fully covered by nonflammable fur. It can withstand any kind of fire attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-50', 'To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-51', 'The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluctuates up and down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-52', 'If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, it reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-53', 'The middle section of its body is called the core. It glows in a different color each time it is seen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-54', 'Their shapes look like hieroglyphs on ancient tablets. It is said that the two are somehow related.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-55', 'Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-56', 'It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a Body Slam.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-57', 'Its feet have suction cups designed to stick to any surface. It tenaciously climbs trees to forage.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-58', 'It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-59', 'Its pleasantly aromatic leaf has the ability to check the humidity and temperature.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-60', 'The moonlight that it stores in the wings on its back apparently gives it the ability to float in midair.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-61', 'It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised, it shoots flames out of its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-62', 'It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children''s are much tastier.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-63', 'Using telepathy only they can employ, they always form a cluster of six Exeggcute.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-64', 'Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent and bite.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-65', 'It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-66', 'It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-67', 'To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. But they do enjoy gentle breezes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-68', 'Looking into its cute, round eyes causes it to sing a relaxing melody, inducing its enemies to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-69', 'It rocks its body rhythmically. It appears to alter the rhythm depending on how it is feeling.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-70', 'Its thin, filmy body is filled with gases that cause constant sniffles, coughs and teary eyes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-71', 'When the weather turns cold, lots of Ledyba gather from everywhere to cluster and keep each other warm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-72', 'For no reason, it jumps and splashes about, making it easy for predators like Pidgeotto to catch it mid-jump.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-73', 'If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-74', 'The end of its tail serves as a buoy that keeps it from drowning, even in a vicious current.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-75', 'It loves anything that shines. It especially adores coins that it picks up and secretly hoards.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-76', 'As its body grows large, large mushrooms named tochukaso start sprouting out of its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-77', 'It swings its long snout around playfully, but because it is so strong, that can be dangerous.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-78', 'It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-79', 'Disliking water, it lives in deep burrows in arid areas. It can roll itself instantly into a ball.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-80', 'A very cautious Pokémon, it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-81', 'It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail, it won''t even notice for a whole day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-82', 'It has an active, playful nature. Many women like to frolic with it because of its affectionate ways.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-83', 'It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-84', 'At night, the center of its body slowly flickers with the same rhythm as a human heartbeat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-85', 'It may plummet from the sky. If attacked by a Spearow, it will violently shake its leaves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-86', 'Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-87', 'If it is attacked by an enemy that is stronger than itself, it feigns injury to fool the enemy and escapes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-88', 'When it walks around on the ground, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-111', 'Legends claim this Pokémon flies the world''s skies continuously on its magnificent, seven-colored wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-112', 'Legends claim this Pokémon flies the world''s skies continuously on its magnificent, seven-colored wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-113', 'It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-114', 'It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss1-123', 'They say that during past strife, Gyarados would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-1', 'Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-2', 'It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-3', 'It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-5', 'Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-6', 'It traps foes with the suction cups on its tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-7', 'Whenever three or more of these get together, they sing in a loud voice that sounds like bellowing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-8', 'The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-9', 'It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-10', 'Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-11', 'In South America, it is said that its right eye sees the future and its left eye views the past.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-12', 'It can take down any opponent with its powerful poison stingers. It sometimes attacks in swarms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-13', 'It deliberately makes itself heavy so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-14', 'The development of wings on its legs enables it to fly fast but also makes it tough to stop and rest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-15', 'It shoots itself suddenly high into the sky, then plummets down in one fell swoop to strike its prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-16', 'With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-17', 'It sleeps deep on the ocean floor to build its energy. It is said to cause tornadoes as it wakes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-18', 'The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea''s surface from a depth of over three miles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-19', 'It''s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect auras, even foes it could not otherwise see.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-20', 'Some legends claim that each of its nine tails has its own unique type of special mystical power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-21', 'Although an energetic, skilled swimmer that uses all of its muscles, it lives on dry land.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-22', 'If approached while asleep, it may awaken and angrily give chase in a groggy state of semi-sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-23', 'Its sweet aroma attracts prey. Then it spews poison. The more toxic it is, the sweeter its aroma.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-24', 'Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than a diamond.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-25', 'You find abandoned coal mines full of them. They dig tirelessly in search of coal.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-26', 'Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-27', 'With its ability to distinguish any aroma, it unfailing finds all food buried deep underground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-28', 'During times of strong sunlight, its bud blooms, its petals open fully, and it becomes very active.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-29', 'When spotted, this Pokémon escapes backward by furiously boring into the ground with its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-30', 'It can drink more than 10 ounces of blood at once. If it has too much, it gets heavy and flies clumsily.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-31', 'A Grotle that lives in the forest is said to have its own secret springwater.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-32', 'Although it is a cocoon, it can move a little. It can extend its poison barb if it is attacked.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-33', 'When two Beldum fuse together, a magnetic nervous system places their brains in union.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-34', 'Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-35', 'The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-36', 'It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-37', 'The skin on most of its body is moist. However, the skin on its belly spiral feels smooth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-38', 'Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-39', 'Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-40', 'Its fin tips leak poison. Its fins and bones are highly valued as ingredients in herbal medicine.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-41', 'They fight each other by locking horns. The herd''s protector takes pride in its battle-scarred horns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-42', 'It is a well-established symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.')
