INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-46', 'It walks around on its tentacles in search of a tree branch where it can dangle down and ambush prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-47', 'It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-48', 'It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-49', 'Its big, developed fins move rapidly, allowing it to swim backward while still facing forward.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-50', 'It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-51', 'It is born deep underground. It can''t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-52', 'It dislikes cold places, so it blows scorching flames to make the environment suitable for itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-53', 'It is extremely ill-tempered. Groups of them will attack any handy target for no reason.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-54', 'It likes playing mischievous tricks such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-55', 'It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-56', 'It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-57', 'It twists and squirms through the ground. The thunderous roar of its tunneling echoes a long way.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-58', 'The direction of its belly spiral differs by area. The equator is thought to have an effect on this.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-59', 'It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike even moving prey from more than 300 feet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-60', 'They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.')
