INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-66', 'The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It''s a highly favored tropical snack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-67', 'Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-68', 'As it develops, its single white tail gains color and splits into six. It is quite warm and cuddly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-69', 'Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss2-70', 'Capable of flying safely in dark places, it emits ultrasonic cries to check for any obstacles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-1', 'Bellossom gather at times and seem to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-2', 'It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy''s actions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-3', 'Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-4', 'Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey… Then its elongated fangs do the rest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-5', 'Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-6', 'Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-7', 'Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-8', 'Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-9', 'As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions, bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-10', 'When agitated, this Pokémon protects itself by spraying poisonous sweat from its pores.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-11', 'It collects data and plans three times as wisely, but it may think too much and fall into a state of immobility.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-12', 'It can generate and release gas within its body. That''s how it can control the altitude of its drift.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-13', 'It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-14', 'It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-15', 'It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-16', 'It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-17', 'When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of sunshine, you''ll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-18', 'It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-19', 'Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-20', 'Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-21', 'After nesting in bramble bushes, the wings of its chicks grow hard from scratches by thorns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-22', 'The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It''s a highly favored tropical snack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-23', 'It raises grubs in the holes in its body. It secretes pheromones to control Combee.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-24', 'It has the world''s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-25', 'It lives in snowy regions. It carves patterns in trees with its claws as a signal to others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-26', 'It stores some of the air it inhales in its internal flame pouch, which heats it to over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-27', 'What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-28', 'It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-29', 'It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory by bashing one another with their steel bodies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-30', 'When two Beldum fuse together, a magnetic nervous system places their brains in union.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-31', 'Its body is made of a powerful poison. Touching it accidentally will cause a fever that requires bed rest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-32', 'With its horns, it digs burrows to sleep in at night. In the morning, damp soil clings to its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-33', 'When its electricity builds, its muscles are stimulated, and it becomes more aggressive than usual.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-34', 'Its whiskers help it to maintain balance. Its fangs never stop growing, so it gnaws to pare them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-35', 'It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-36', 'When it moves, it leaves only a blur. If it hides in grass, its protective colors make it invisible.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-37', 'It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail, but the stench dulls after a few squirts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-38', 'Naturally dull to begin with, it lost its ability to feel pain due to Shellder''s seeping poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-39', 'It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-40', 'Their shapes look like hieroglyphs on ancient tablets. It is said that the two are somehow related.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-41', 'When Vaporeon''s fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-42', 'When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-43', 'The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground''s natural magnetism, letting it float.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-44', 'At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a thousand, packed closely together in a lump.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-45', 'By alternately raising and lowering its two heads, it balances itself to be more stable while running.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-46', 'It is whispered that any child who mistakes Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-47', 'It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-48', 'Its irregularly configured DNA is affected by its surroundings. It evolves if its environment changes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-49', 'It flies straight at its target''s face then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-50', 'Wherever Grimer has passed, so many germs are left behind that no plants will ever grow again.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-51', 'Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-52', 'If it starts kicking repeatedly, both legs will stretch even longer to strike a fleeing foe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-53', 'It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-54', 'To corner prey, they check each other''s location using barks that only they can understand.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-55', 'It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-56', 'It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-57', 'It loves to bite and yank people''s hair from behind without warning, just to see their shocked reactions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-58', 'Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-59', 'It is said that when chased, it lures its attacker onto dark mountain trails where the foe will get lost.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-60', 'Awakened by moonlight, it roams actively at night. In the day it stays quietly underground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-61', 'This intelligent Pokémon roasts hard berries with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-62', 'It hangs and waits for flying insect prey to come near. It does not move about much on its own.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-63', 'It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn''t bother it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-64', 'Living wherever there is food available, it ceaselessly scavenges for edibles the entire day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-65', 'It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-66', 'A sweet sap leaks from its tail''s tip. Although not nutritious, the tail is pleasant to chew on.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-67', 'A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-68', 'Vicious in nature, it drives Pidgey from their nests and scavenges any leftovers it can find.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-69', 'The foul fluid from its rear is so revolting that it can make people feel queasy up to a mile and a quarter away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss3-70', 'A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-1', 'You can tell its age by the length of its iron horns. It claims an entire mountain as its territory.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-2', 'It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic humming makes you feel like you''re in a dream.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-3', 'This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-4', 'It attacks people and Pokémon that cross the desert. This has only furthered its bad reputation.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-5', 'A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice dating back 10,000 years. This Pokémon has been around a long, long, long time.')
