INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-18', 'This marine Pokémon has an impressive build that lets it freely fly over raging seas without trouble.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-19', 'Extremely powerful, they can dig through even the hardest ground to a depth of over 60 miles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-20', 'As its electric charge amplifies, blue sparks begin to crackle between its horns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-21', 'Even in the most vicious storm, this Pokémon plays happily if thunder rumbles in the sky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-22', 'When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-23', 'It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-24', 'By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly, it produces a captivating sound.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-25', 'It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-26', 'It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-27', 'It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-28', 'It uses its scaly, rugged body to seal the entrance of its nest and protect its young from predators.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-29', 'It spreads its beautiful wings wide to frighten its enemies. It can fly at Mach 2 speed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-30', 'It can swim at speeds of 75 mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-31', 'It is the largest of all identified Pokémon. They jump as a pack to herd their prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-32', 'Its crystalline orbs appear to give this Pokémon the power to freely control the weather.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-33', 'Its body constantly discharges electricity. Getting close to it will make your hair stand on end.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-34', 'It is dangerous. If it has too much electricity and has nothing to do, it amuses itself by exploding.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-35', 'Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-36', 'If it is safe, the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-37', 'It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory by bashing one another with their steel bodies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-38', 'It has space in its throat to store saliva. It can also roll up its tongue and store it in the same spot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-39', 'Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places, you would give a Luvdisc to someone you love.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-40', 'It always goes at its full power, but this very tough and durable Pokémon never gets tired.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-41', 'It is found in volcanic craters. Its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit, so don''t underestimate it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-42', 'The fiery surface of its body gives off a wavering, rippling glare that is similar to the sun.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-43', 'The Magnemite are united by a magnetism so powerful, it dries all moisture in its vicinity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-44', 'It has been seen pounding boulders with the bone it carries in order to tap out messages to others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-45', 'It has a calm and caring nature. Because its horn grows slowly, it prefers not to fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-46', 'Quick to anger, it stabs enemies with its horn to inject a powerful poison when it becomes agitated.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-47', 'It renders its prey immobile using well-developed claws, then carries the prey more than 60 miles to its nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-48', 'Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-49', 'Further research enhanced its abilities. Sometimes, it may exhibit motions that were not programmed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-50', 'In battle, it extends all 80 of its tentacles to entrap its opponent inside a poisonous net.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-51', 'Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-52', 'It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-53', 'Even though it is filled with acid, it does not melt because it also oozes a protective fluid.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-54', 'The beat of its wings is so powerful that it accidentally dislodges full-grown trees when it takes off in flight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-55', 'Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-56', 'When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-57', 'Even though its body is extremely skinny, it is blindingly fast when catching its prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-58', 'Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor''s back contained a mysterious power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-59', 'They form packs to attack boats and rip out their hulls to sink them. They live in rivers in the jungle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-60', 'If it is sad or lonely, the skull it wears shakes and emits a plaintive and mournful sound.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-61', 'If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-62', 'This Pokémon is full of life energy. It continually sheds its skin and grows steadily larger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-63', 'Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-64', 'Its fragrance attracts a swarm of Volbeat, so they draw over 200 patterns in the night sky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-65', 'When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-66', 'Its long tongue, slathered with a gooey saliva, sticks to anything, so it is very useful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-67', 'Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-68', 'The units at the sides of its body generate antigravity energy to keep it aloft in the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-69', 'Although not very combative, it will torment its foes with poison spikes if it is threatened in any way.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-70', 'It raises its big ears to check its surroundings. It will strike first if it senses any danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-71', 'Common in grassy areas and forests, it is very docile and will chase off enemies by flapping up sand.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-72', 'It is a weak runner immediately after birth. It gradually becomes faster by chasing after its parents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-73', 'A manmade Pokémon that came about as a result of research. It is programmed with only basic motions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-74', 'It has mystical powers but doesn''t recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-75', 'It uses its horn to feed on envy and malice, or so it''s said. It''s very active at night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-76', 'It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-77', 'It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-78', 'Its wings bring cottony clouds to mind. It grooms with springwater and loves to sit on heads.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-79', 'It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-80', 'It drifts aimlessly in waves. Very difficult to see in water, it may not be noticed until it stings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-81', 'Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches and eats small bugs at night that are attracted by light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-82', 'It emits light from its tail to communicate. It loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-83', 'It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hgss4-84', 'Its large eyes can scan 360 degrees. It looks in all directions to seek out insects as its prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS01', 'A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind when it flies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS02', 'It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS03', 'It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS04', 'To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS05', 'It has a perfect sense of time. Whatever happens, it keeps rhythm by precisely tilting its head in time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS06', 'When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS10', 'It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS11', 'It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS12', 'Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS13', 'Its lips are the most sensitive part of its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS14', 'It ferries people across the sea on its back. It may sing an enchanting cry if it is in a good mood.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS15', 'It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS16', 'It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS17', 'Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS19', 'The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS20', 'Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Unable to contain its sheer power, it races headlong around the land.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS21', 'Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS22', 'It is a manmade Pokémon. Since it doesn''t breathe, people are eager to try it in any environment..')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS23', 'This upgraded version of Porygon is designed for space exploration. It can''t fly, though.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS24', 'Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('hsp-HGSS25', 'If it starts kicking repeatedly, both legs will stretch even longer to strike a fleeing foe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-1', 'It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-2', 'It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-3', 'It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-4', 'It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-5', 'Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokémon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-6', 'Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-7', 'It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-8', 'It moves along below the sand''s surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-9', 'It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-10', 'The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-11', 'These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd11-12', 'It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-1', 'They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-2', 'This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-3', 'The Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-4', 'When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-5', 'Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-6', 'The energy made in its cheeks'' electric pouches is stored inside its membranes and released while it is gliding.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-7', 'Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-8', 'It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-9', 'They steal from people for fun, but their victims can''t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-10', 'Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-11', 'Spinning minigears are rotated at high speed and repeatedly fired away. It is dangerous if the gears don''t return.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd12-12', 'They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-1', 'Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-2', 'The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-3', 'Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-4', 'It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-5', 'It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-6', 'Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-7', 'Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-8', 'It has an active, playful nature. Many women like to frolic with it because of its affectionate ways.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-9', 'To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-10', 'They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-11', 'These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd14-12', 'Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-1', 'Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-2', 'It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-3', 'A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-4', 'It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-5', 'To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-6', 'It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-7', 'It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-8', 'It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-9', 'It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-10', 'The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-11', 'A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd15-12', 'It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-1', 'While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-2', 'A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-3', 'Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-4', 'In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-5', 'It is small but rough and tough. It won''t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-6', 'It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-7', 'Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling it skin up to its neck.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-8', 'It captivates foes with its huge, round eyes, then lulls them to sleep by singing a soothing melody.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-9', 'A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-10', 'Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-11', 'Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd16-12', 'Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-1', 'This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-2', 'They often gather near places frequented by electric Pokémon in order to avoid being attacked by bird Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-3', 'While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-4', 'This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It''s famous for being a hard worker.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-5', 'A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-6', 'Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-7', 'It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-8', 'This Pokémon was not originally found in Alola. Human actions caused a surge in their numbers, and they went feral. They''re prideful and crafty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-9', 'Its head sports an altered form of whiskers made of metal. When in communication with its comrades, its whiskers wobble to and fro.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-10', 'It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it''s able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-11', 'This Pokémon feeds on berries, whose leftover seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it fires off from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd17-12', 'With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-1', 'It''s both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-2', 'As a result of headaches so fierce they cause it to cry, it sometimes uses psychokinesis without meaning to.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-3', 'Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-4', 'A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-5', 'Its long tail often breaks off. It doesn''t really feel any pain, though, and the tail grows back, so Slowpoke isn''t particularly bothered.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-6', 'It loves working out. As it gazes at its muscles, which continue to swell day by day, it becomes more and more dedicated to its training.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-7', 'When it thinks of its deceased mother, it weeps loudly. Mandibuzz that hear its cries will attack it from the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-8', 'It sends out electromagnetic waves, which let it float through the air. Touching it while it''s eating electricity will give you a full-body shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-9', 'After a 10-hour struggle, a fisherman was able to pull one up and confirm its existence.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-10', 'The eggs laid by Chansey are rich in nutrients and a favorite food of many Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-11', 'Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd18-12', 'Roughly 20 years ago, it was artificially created, utilizing the latest technology of the time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-1', 'A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-2', 'It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-3', 'Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-4', 'It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-5', 'It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-6', 'The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-7', 'This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-8', 'When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-9', 'The flame on its tail indicates Charmander''s life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-10', 'It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-11', 'A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-12', 'The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-13', 'It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-14', 'Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-15', 'While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-16', 'A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon''s body. Once that happens, it''s ready to fight at full power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-17', 'It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-18', 'It is small but rough and tough. It won''t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-19', 'To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-20', 'Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-21', 'It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-22', 'It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-23', 'This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It''s famous for being a hard worker.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-24', 'When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won''t be able to resist weeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('mcd21-25', 'Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-1', 'The tail''s tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-2', 'By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-3', 'Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-4', 'When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-5', 'It is hard for it to support its own weight out of water, so it gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-6', 'This powerful Pokémon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies'' bellies, then lifts and throws them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-7', 'Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores to float, even around the world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-8', 'It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-9', 'It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea, because its powers are too strong.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-10', 'Meganium''s breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-11', 'The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-12', 'Despite its small size, it can zap even adult humans. However, if it does so, it also surprises itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-13', 'Its sturdy wings look heavy, but they are actually hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-14', 'When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke''s head and unlocked an extraordinary power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-15', 'Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than a diamond.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-16', 'They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-17', 'If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-18', 'It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-20', 'Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-21', 'It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its tackle is strong enough to knock down a house.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-22', 'It rotates its arms to generate electricity, but it tires easily, so it charges up only a little bit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-23', 'Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-24', 'It is said that when chased, it lures its attacker onto dark mountain trails where the foe will get lost.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-25', 'Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-26', 'Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-27', 'It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It''s hard to tell which end is which.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-28', 'A spicy aroma emanates from around its neck. The aroma acts as a stimulant to restore health.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-29', 'The scent of spices comes from around its neck. Somehow, sniffing it makes you want to fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-30', 'The moonlight that it stores in the wings on its back apparently gives it the ability to float in midair.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-31', 'If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-32', 'It opens its huge jaws wide when attacking. If it loses any fangs while biting, they grow back in.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-33', 'Electricity runs across the surface of its body. In darkness, its entire body glows a whitish-blue.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-34', 'As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won''t grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-35', 'It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-36', 'What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-37', 'It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-38', 'The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea''s surface from a depth of over three miles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-39', 'When the stars flicker in the night sky, Ledian flutters about, scattering a glowing powder.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-40', 'It dislikes cold places, so it blows scorching flames to make the environment suitable for itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-41', 'Its milk is packed with nutrition, making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-42', 'Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-43', 'It swings its long snout around playfully, but, because it is so strong, that can be dangerous.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-44', 'Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-45', 'Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on boulders and boat hulls as it swims.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-46', 'This Pokémon is fully covered by nonflammable fur. It can withstand any kind of fire attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-47', 'Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-48', 'An examination of its cells revealed the presence of a gene not found in Horsea. It became a hot topic.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-49', 'The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluctuates up and down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-50', 'It converts sunlight into energy. In the darkness after sunset, it closes its petals and becomes still.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-51', 'A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-52', 'They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-53', 'A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up the sun''s rays.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-54', 'Its pleasantly aromatic leaf has the ability to check the humidity and temperature.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-55', 'It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-56', 'It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised, it shoots flames out of its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-57', 'It is timid and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-58', 'Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent and bite.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-59', 'It flies straight at its target''s face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-60', 'It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast that the movement can rarely be seen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-61', 'To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. They do enjoy gentle breezes, though.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-62', 'If attacked by a larger enemy, it quickly swims to safety by adeptly controlling its dorsal fin.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-63', 'It is very timid. It''s afraid to move if alone, but it''s active if in a group.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-64', 'Swimming freely in open seas, it may fly out of the water and over the waves if it builds up enough speed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-65', 'If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-66', 'The end of its tail serves as a buoy that keeps it from drowning, even in a vicious current.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-67', 'Because its wings aren''t yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-68', 'Awakened by moonlight, it roams actively at night. In the day it stays quietly underground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-69', 'It twists and squirms through the ground. The thunderous roar of its tunneling echoes a long way.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-70', 'It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-71', 'A very cautious Pokémon, it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-72', 'The Berries it stores in its vaselike shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-73', 'It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail, it won''t even notice for a whole day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-74', 'Although it looks frightening, it is actually kind and affectionate. It is very popular.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-75', 'It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-76', 'The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-77', 'Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears to be closer to a rock than a plant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-78', 'It may drop out of the sky suddenly. If attacked by a Spearow, it violently shakes its leaves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-79', 'It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-80', 'It is small but rough and tough. It won''t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-81', 'Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo1-82', 'This Pokémon lives in cold water. It leaves the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo2-1', 'It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy''s actions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo2-2', 'Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo2-3', 'If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dancelike kicks, you may get drilled hard.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('neo2-4', 'Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.')
