INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-8', 'It habitually digs up and hoards gems in its nest. Its loot is constantly targeted by thieves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-9', 'It is very conscious of its looks and never fails to groom its ears. It runs with sprightly jumps.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-10', 'It makes electricity with pouches in its cheeks and shoots charges from its tail. It live atop trees.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-11', 'It plays with others by touching tails and setting off sparks. This appears to be a test of courage.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-12', 'When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-13', 'Its fiery rear end is fueld by gas made in its belly. Even rain can''t extinguish the fire.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-14', 'Its nests is small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-15', 'If it looses crackling power from the electric pouches on its cheeks, it is being wary.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-16', 'It lives along shores in northern countries. A skilled swimmer, it dives for over 10 minutes to hunt.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('pop9-17', 'It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-1', 'This Pokémon''s body is covered by fine hairs that can be seen only under a microscope.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-2', 'This Pokémon searches for food while flying at Mach 2. Its large claws make fearsome weapons.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-3', 'This Pokémon burrows through the earth at high speed, looking for food. The tunnels it digs are used by Diglett as nests.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-4', 'This Pokémon is still immature. When threatened, it releases poison from its head and tries to drive its enemies away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-5', 'A sure sign spring is on its way is when the seed on this Pokémon''s back flowers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-6', 'This Pokémon sometimes hunts for food in rivers, swimming using the small webs between the toes on its rear legs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-7', 'When it senses enemies approaching, this Pokémon releases an orange fluid from the joints in its legs and flees.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-8', 'After lulling its enemies with its large eyes, this Pokémon sings them to sleep with a relaxing melody.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-9', 'The poison scales on its wings are waterproof, allowing this Pokémon to be active even on rainy days.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-10', 'This Pokémon attacks its prey with its eighty toxin-producing tentacles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-11', 'This Pokémon''s fur repels water like a duck''s feathers, allowing it to stay dry and fluffy even in water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-12', 'This gentle Pokémon can understand human language and allows people to ride on its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-13', 'This Pokémon has a unique cry, as all three of its heads are always talking independently of one another.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-14', 'Its nonchalant reaction to everything somehow gives this Pokémon an imposing presence.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-15', 'When attacked, this Pokémon withdraws into its shell, although it can''t quite pull in all of its long tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-16', 'This Pokémon uses its six-foot tongue as if it were a hand. The origin of its anaesthetic properties is still a mystery.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-17', 'This Pokémon makes a loud jangling noise when it shakes its petals to spread poison powder.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('si1-18', 'This Pokémon only calms down when there are no other animals or people around—which means no one has ever seen it when it''s not angry.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-1', 'When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-2', 'Its shell is filled with its soft innards. It doesn''t move much because of the risk it might carelessly spill its innards out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-3', 'Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-4', 'No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-5', 'The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-6', 'One solid blow from its horns is enough to split apart a large tree. Its greatest rival in Alola is Vikavolt.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-7', 'When this Pokémon senses danger, a sweet fluid oozes from the tip of its heads. The taste of it disgusts bird Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-8', 'Its wings and antennae don''t cope well with moisture. After a rain, it faces sunward to dry off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-9', 'This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-10', 'A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-11', 'It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-13', 'They often gather near places frequented by electric Pokémon in order to avoid being attacked by bird Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-14', 'They give off a sweet and refreshing scent. Cutiefly often gather near the tall grass where Fomantis are hiding.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-16', 'As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-17', 'It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-18', 'A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-19', 'The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-20', 'Its long, striking legs aren''t just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-21', 'It''s both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-22', 'Overflowing with beauty and majesty, this strong Pokémon appears in ancient Eastern folklore.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-23', 'Coal is the source of Torkoal''s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mounts where they live.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-24', 'While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-25', 'At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-26', 'This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it''s not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer''s orders with complete nonchalance.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-28', 'As a result of headaches so fierce they cause it to cry, it sometimes uses psychokinesis without meaning to.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-29', 'It is said that the red part of its forehead grants supernatural powers to those who posses one, so it was over-hunted in the past.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-30', 'It''s still not very good at walking. Its Trainers should train this Pokémon to walk every day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-31', 'It marches over the land in search of bug Pokémon to eat. Then it takes them underwater so it can dine on them where it''s safe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-32', 'Its percentage of body fat is nearly zero. Its body is entirely muscle, which makes it heavy and forces its swimming prowess to develop.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-33', 'The hardness of its shell surpasses the hardness of a diamond. In days gone by, people used the shells to make shields.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-34', 'Its hard shell cannot be shattered—not even by a bomb. The contents of the shell remain unknown.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-36', 'Pursued by Mareanie for the branches on its head, this Pokémon will sometimes snap its own branches off as a diversion while it escapes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-37', 'Fishermen keep an eye out for Wingull in the sky, because wherever they''re circling, the ocean sure to be is teeming with fish Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-38', 'Gathering food is the work of young males. They store food in their capacious beaks and carry it back to others waiting in the nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-39', 'This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It''s famous for being a hard worker.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-40', 'A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards it enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-41', 'It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learning from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-43', 'It just throws punches indiscriminately. In times of desperation, it can lop off its own pincers and fire them like rockets.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-44', 'When it''s in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-45', 'It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-46', 'It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-47', 'It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-48', 'It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder''s shell is no match for it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-49', 'It lives in the depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-50', 'This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-51', 'From the food it digests, it generates electricity, and it stores this energy in its electric sac.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-52', 'It produces electricity via an electrical organ in its abdomen. It overwhelms bird Pokémon with shocking beams of electrical energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-53', 'The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-54', 'It sleeps in caves during the day. It has no eyes, so to check its surroundings while flying, it emits ultrasonic waves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-55', 'Its thick fangs are hollow like straws, making them unexpectedly fragile. These fangs are specialized for sucking blood.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-56', 'Both its legs became wings, and as a result, it can''t move well on the ground. All it can do is crawl around.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-57', 'The crystals on Grimer''s body are lumps of toxins. If one falls off, lethal poisons leak out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-58', 'While it''s unexpectedly quiet and friendly, if it''s not fed any trash for a while, it will smash its Trainer''s furnishings and eat up the fragments.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-59', 'It finds really fun dreams tasty. When it makes friends with people, it may show them the most delicious dreams it''s ever eaten.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-60', 'As a matter of course, it makes anyone it meets fall asleep and has a taste of their dreams. Anyone having a good dream, it carries off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-62', 'It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-63', 'Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-64', 'Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-65', 'Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-67', 'It was originally brought in from another region, but now Makuhita from Alola are more famous.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-68', 'It is known for its fantastic strength, but as it grows older, it focuses more on training Makuhita.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-69', 'The hexagonal cavity is its ear. It walks in the direction of sounds it hears, but if the sounds cease, it panics and topples over.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-70', 'It explores caves in search of underground water. It''s not comfortable around water, so this Pokémon takes great care in lapping it up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-71', 'Known for its hefty horsepower, this Pokémon is a popular partner for construction workers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-72', 'It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-73', 'They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-74', 'It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-75', 'Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-76', 'When the sun goes down, it becomes active. It runs around town on a chase for good food for the boss of its nest—Raticate.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-77', 'This gourmet Pokémon is particular about the taste and freshness of its food. Restaurants where Raticate live have a good reputation.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-78', 'This Pokémon was not originally found in Alola. Human actions caused a surge in their numbers, and they went feral. They''re prideful and crafty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-79', 'Its round face and smooth coat—softer than the most high-class velvet—have made this a very popular Pokémon in Alola.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-81', 'If they scent the faintest trace of blood, they rush to attack en masse. When alone, they''re rather cowardly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-82', 'It has a sad history. In the past, its dorsal fin was a treasured foodstuff, so this Pokémon became a victim of overfishing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-83', 'It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-84', 'They move in groups of a few individuals. A female is often the leader of the group, and the males will gather food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-85', 'Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-86', 'Its head sports an altered form of whiskers made of metal. When in communication with its comrades, its whiskers wobble to and fro.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-87', 'Its shining gold hair provides it with protection. It''s reputed that keeping any of its fallen hairs will bring bad luck.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-88', 'Its feathers, which fall off as it grows, are thin and sharp. In times long past, warriors used them as swords.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-90', 'Its growls make its opponents uneasy. This laid-back Pokémon tends to sleep half the day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-91', 'More timid than Snubbull, this Pokémon is doted on by young people amused at the contrast between its looks and its attitude.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-92', 'It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it''s able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-93', 'It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-94', 'After a 10-hour struggle, a fisherman was able to pull one up and confirm its existence.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-95', 'From time immemorial, it has been venerated by agricultural peoples as an entity able to control the weather.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-96', 'Incur the wrath of this normally calm Pokémon at your peril, because it will smash everything to smithereens before it''s satisfied.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-97', 'Farmers whose fields are troubled by bug Pokémon appreciate Spearow for its vigorous appetite and look after it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-98', 'Drawings of a Pokémon resembling Fearow can be seen in murals from deep in ancient history.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-99', 'Kangaskhan''s maternal love is so deep that it will brave death to protect its offspring.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-101', 'Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-101a', 'Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-102', 'Its steps are staggering and unsteady, but Spinda thinks it''s walking in a straight line.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-103', 'Because it doesn''t yelp, it''s extremely popular with Trainers who live in apartment buildings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-104', 'Its dense black fur grows continuously. The high cost of keeping its hard fur properly groomed make this a troublesome Pokémon to train.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-105', 'Intelligent, good-natured, and valiant, it''s a trustworthy partner on rescue teams.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-106', 'This Pokémon feeds on berries, whose leftover seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it fires off from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-107', 'By bending its beak, it can produce a variety of call and brand itself a noisy nuisance for its neighbors.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-108', 'Within its beak, its internal gas ignites, explosively launching seeds with enough power to pulverize boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-109', 'With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-111', 'Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-112', 'This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm1-113', 'Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-2', 'Perhaps because it would like to grow up quickly, it has a voracious appetite, eating a hundred leaves a day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-3', 'Its shell is filled with a thick liquid. All of the cells throughout its body are being rebuilt in preparation for evolution.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-4', 'Its wings are covered in toxic scales. If it finds bird Pokémon going after Caterpie, Butterfree sprinkles its scales on them to drive them off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-5', 'During the day, It stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-6', 'During the day, It stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-7', 'Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-8', 'The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-9', 'Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-10', 'Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-11', 'The scales it scatters will paralyze anyone who touches them, making that person unable to stand.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-13', 'Even though its body is extremely skinny, it is blindingly fast when catching its prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-14', 'The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-15', 'Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-16', 'Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-17', 'It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-18', 'If you find its nest, you shouldn''t stick your hand inside. You''ll get bitten by an irritated Grubbin.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-19', 'This Ultra Beast''s body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-21', 'While it''s quite friendly toward humans once it''s grown used to them, in the wild it must be quite fierce to defend its territory from Rockruff.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-22', 'Legends tell of its fighting alongside a general and conquering a whole country.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-23', 'Darumaka''s droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-24', 'When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-25', 'It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It''s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-26', 'If you try too hard to get close to it, it won''t open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-27', 'If you try too hard to get close to it, it won''t open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-28', 'It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokémon, its sharp claws can leave its Trainer''s whole body covered in scratches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-29', 'Although it''s rough mannered and egotistical, it finds beating down unworthy opponents boring. It gets motivated for stronger opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-30', 'The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can''t evolve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-31', 'Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-32', 'It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It''s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-33', 'It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-34', 'When tapped, this Pokémon will pull in its head, but its tail will still stick out a little bit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-36', 'Despite the danger, it wants to come up on land. So it does its best to waddle along, but when an enemy finds it, it rushes back to the water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-37', 'Despite the danger, it wants to come up on land. So it does its best to waddle along, but when an enemy finds it, it rushes back to the water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-38', 'Although it has become capable of living on land, it spends its time in the water, where its prey, fish Pokémon, are plentiful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-39', 'It''s quite a gifted swimmer, even among Water-type Pokémon, but it normally spends its time on land.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-40', 'It drifts through the sea searching for prey. Its poisonous tentacles break off sometimes, but after a while, they grow back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-41', 'It fires off ultrasonic waves from its red orbs to weaken its prey, and then it wraps them up in its 80 tentacles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-42', 'There are some places where Slowpoke is worshiped because of a long-standing belief that whenever Slowpoke yawns, it rains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-43', 'Spacing out is basically all it does. It turns back into Slowpoke if its tail, along with Shellder, breaks off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-44', 'It has always been supposed that Seel live only in cold seas. Their having shown up in Alola is a mystery.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-45', 'It swims through the ocean at a speed of eight knots, searching for Pokémon that will become its prey. It''s especially fond of Wishiwashi.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-46', 'If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-47', 'Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-48', 'Although known for their splendid tail fins, Goldeen apparently compete among themselves to see whose horn is thickest and sharpest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-49', 'Its horn spins like a drill to steadily hollow out rocks—even harder ones. The coloration of the male is more vivid.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-50', 'This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-51', 'It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-52', 'It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-53', 'The tradition known as Pyukumuku chucking started from the custom of throwing Pyukumuku back into the sea after they wash onshore.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-54', 'Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-55', 'As electricity builds up inside its body, it becomes more aggressive. One theory is that the electricity buildup is actually causing stress.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-56', 'Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-58', 'It buries itself in fallen leaves and barely moves, munching away on humus. If you accidentally step on one, you''ll get a shock!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-59', 'It has an organ that generates electricity in its abdomen. It concentrates energy in its strong jaws and fires off powerful jolts of electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-60', 'It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they''ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-62', 'By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-63', 'The latest research has determined that there are over 20 possible arrangements of the patterns on its stomach.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-64', 'It has no eyeballs, so it can''t see. It checks its surroundings via the ultrasonic waves it emits from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-65', 'Every once in a while, you''ll see a Golbat that''s missing some fangs. This happens when hunger drives it to try biting a Steel-type Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-66', 'Its fangs are so sharp, if it bites you in the dark and sucks your blood, you won''t notice any pain or realize you''ve been bitten.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-67', 'It''s said that gas emanating from a graveyard was possessed by the grievances of the deceased and thus became a Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-68', 'It''s said that gas emanating from a graveyard was possessed by the grievances of the deceased and thus became a Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-69', 'On moonless nights, Haunter searches for someone to curse, so it''s best not to go out walking around.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-70', 'You can hear tales told all over the world about how Gengar will pay a visit to children who are naughty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-71', 'It can be spotted near recreational facilities, intending to eat the pleasant dreams of children who enjoyed themselves there that day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-72', 'In Alola, Komala is Hypno''s main target. It rarely harms people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-73', 'Its thin, balloon-like body is inflated by horribly toxic gases. It reeks when it is nearby.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-74', 'If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-75', 'It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-76', 'Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-77', 'What gives meaning to its life is surprising others. If you set your ear against the red orbs around its neck, you can hear shrieking.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-78', 'Feared for its wrath and the curses it spreads, this Pokémon will also, on a whim, cast spells that help people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-79', 'The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-80', 'When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-81', 'It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it''s imitating.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-83', 'It lives in areas of limited rainfall. When danger approaches, it curls up into a ball to protect its soft stomach.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-84', 'Its claws and horns often break off. The broken claws and horns can be used to carve plows for tilling farm fields.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-85', 'It travels through tunnels that it digs underground. It hates sunlight, so it comes out only after the sun goes down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-86', 'While the three of them normally get along splendidly, on rare occasions a huge fight will break out over which head gets to eat first.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-87', 'Geodude that have lived a long life have had all their edges smoothed out until they''re totally round. They also have a calm, quiet disposition.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-88', 'It climbs up cliffs as it heads toward the peak of a mountain. As soon as it reaches the summit, it rolls back down the way it came.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-89', 'When Golem grow old, they stop shedding their shells. Those that have lived a long, long time have shells green with moss.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-90', 'At night, it weeps loudly for its dead mother, but those cries only attract its natural enemy—Mandibuzz.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-91', 'It throws bones at Mandibuzz to knock it down. It''s thought that Marowak is trying to avenge its parent.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-92', 'Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging Tackles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-93', 'Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging Tackles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-94', 'Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degress Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-95', 'From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude. Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-96', 'This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-97', 'It has a sluggish nature. It lies at the river''s bottom, waiting for prey to stray into its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-98', 'It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-99', 'It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-100', 'It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-101', 'It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by 10.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-102', 'It knows how people and Pokémon feel by looking at their auras. It doesn''t approach dangerous opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-103', 'Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-104', 'Its hard pincers are well suited to both offense and defense. Fights between two Crabrawler are like boxing matches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-105', 'It stores coldness in its pincers and pummels its foes. It can even smash thick walls of ice to bits!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-106', 'It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-108', 'It has a weakness for shiny things. It''s been known to sneak into the nests of Gabite—noted collectors of jewels—in search of treasure.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-110', 'They''re such cowards that they won''t hunt alone. When five or so of them get together, they suddenly turn ferocious!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-111', 'People believe that carrying one of its discarded fangs will prevent mishaps at sea, so the fangs are made into accessories.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-112', 'A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-113', 'Alola, where it''s warm all year round, is a comfortable environment for this Pokémon. Sometimes you''ll even see it outside of deserts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-114', 'Alola, where it''s warm all year round, is a comfortable environment for this Pokémon. Sometimes you''ll even see it outside of deserts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-115', 'Krokorok really hates it when its body gets cold. On nights when the temperature drops, it digs deep into the desert sands.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-116', 'When it spots prey, even at a distance of over 30 miles, it swims through the desert as if it were water, then jumps out and chomps them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-117', 'It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-118', 'It draws prey near with its blinking lights and then wraps them up in its long tentacles and holds them in place.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-119', 'When it comes to strong hypnosis, there''s an endless number of people who utilize Malamar for their nefarious deeds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-121', 'Although it''s powerful enough to dig right through volcanic rock, it doesn''t allow itself to be seen very often.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-122', 'Its metallic whiskers are heavy, so it''s not very fast, but it has the power to dig through bedrock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-123', 'It usually lives deep in mountains. However, hunger may drive it to eat railroad tracks and cars.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-124', 'It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory by bashing one another with their steel bodies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-125', 'It claims an entire mountain as its own. The more wounds it has, the more it has battled, so don''t take it lightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-126', 'It concentrates its mental energy and fires off mysterious waves called auras, which can crush boulders of large size to dust.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-127', 'This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-128', 'It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-129', 'Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-131', 'On nights with many shooting stars, they gather in packs and dance in circles. If you should see them, something good will happen!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-132', 'They''re popular, but they''re rare. Trainers who show them off recklessly may be targeted by thieves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-133', 'It can''t help but hear a pin drop from over half a mile away, so it lives deep in the mountains where there aren''t many people or Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-134', 'Recordings of Jigglypuff''s strange lullabies can be purchased from department stores. These CDs can be found near the bedding area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-135', 'Thanks to its bouncy body and fine fur, this Pokémon is sought after. Holding one in your arms while you sleep feels great.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-136', 'The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-137', 'It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-138', 'As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions, bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-139', 'To protect itself, it shoots cotton from its body. When it gets wet in the rain, its cotton grows moist and heavy, and it can''t move as well.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-141', 'It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-142', 'It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-143', 'Its incisors grow continuously throughout its life. If its incisors get too long, this Pokémon becomes unable to eat, and it starves to death.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-144', 'People say that it fled from its enemies by using its small webbed hind feet to swim from island to island in Alola.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-145', 'Its reckless nature leads it to stand up to others—even large Pokémon—if it has to protect its territory.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-146', 'Carrying food through Fearow''s territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-147', 'When visiting a junkyard, you may catch sight of it having an intense fight with Murkrow over shiny objects.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-148', 'Although the jewel on its forehead appears to be a different color than those of Alolan Persian, it''s mostly made of the same material.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-150', 'A two-headed Pokémon that was discovered as a sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-151', 'An enemy that takes its eyes off any of the three heads—even for a second—will get pecked severely.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-152', 'It checks out whatever''s around it by licking everything. If you don''t clean off a spot where it''s licked you, you''ll break out in a rash!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-153', 'A contest is under way to determine which one can stick its tongue out the farthest. The current record is…more than 82 feet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-154', 'This Pokémon was created using the cutting-edge science of 20 years ago, so many parts of it have since become obsolete.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-155', 'This Pokémon was created using the cutting-edge science of 20 years ago, so many parts of it have since become obsolete.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-156', 'AI has been installed in it. It learns various things all on its own, but it even remembers things it doesn''t need to know.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-157', 'Its behavior is noticeably unstable, which is apparently due to the incompetence of the engineer who updated its programming.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-158', 'It doesn''t do anything other than eat and sleep. When prompted to make a serious effort, though, it apparently displays awesome power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-159', 'It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-160', 'It would claim another Pokémon''s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-161', 'Usually it''s a well-behaved Pokémon, but if you take its round rock away, it will cry and fuss and throw a big old tantrum.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm10-162', 'It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it''s one of them. This way they won''t attack it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-2', 'Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won''t miss prey—even those behind it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-3', 'It prefers to battle by biting apart foes'' heads instantly while flying by at high speed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-4', 'This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-5', 'It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-6', 'This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-7', 'This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-8', 'Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-9', 'Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-10', 'It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-11', 'It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-12', 'These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-13', 'It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-14', 'They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-15', 'When the sun rises, Fomantis spreads its four leaves and bathes in the sunlight. The tip of its head has a pleasant aroma.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-16', 'For self-protection, it pretends to be a bug Pokémon. Both of its arms bear keen-edged petals.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-17', 'Because of its sweet, delicious aroma, bird Pokémon are always after it, but it''s not intelligent enough to care.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-18', 'It''s protected by its hard sepals, so it plays with bird Pokémon without worry. They peck it relentlessly, but it doesn''t care.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-19', 'A master of grand and beautiful kicks, it can knock out even kickboxing champions with a single blow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-20', 'It wraps its prey in green seaweed and sucks away their vitality. It only likes to go after big prey like Wailord.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-21', 'Its entire body is burning. When it breathes, the temperature rises. When it sneezes, flames shoot out!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-22', 'There are still quite a few factories that rely on the flames provided by Magmortar to process metals.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-23', 'Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-24', 'The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years—or whenever it becomes really angry.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-26', 'This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-27', 'While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-28', 'While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-29', 'The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-30', 'Being consumed in Chandelure''s flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-31', 'It scatters embers in the tall grass. Then bug Pokémon, frightened by the flames, come flying out, and Fletchinder gobbles them up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-32', 'Its tough wings don''t allow fire to pass through them. A long time ago, firefighters'' outfits were made from Talonflame wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-33', 'The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can''t evolve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-34', 'Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-36', 'It likes swimming around with people on its back. In the Alola region, it''s an important means of transportation over water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-37', 'It feeds mainly on ice and snow. It''s only able to survive in a limited number of places in the warm Alola region.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-38', 'It freezes hikers who have come to climb snowy mountains and carries them back to its home. It only goes after men it thinks are handsome.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-39', 'When night falls, their pink patterns begin to shine. They''re popular with divers, so there are resorts that feed them to keep them close.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-40', 'Deep down at the bottom of the ocean, prey is scarce. Lumineon get into fierce disputes with Lanturn over food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-41', 'During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain''s lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.')
