INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-43', 'Savage, violent Pokémon, red and blue Basculin are always fighting each other over territory.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-44', 'It was restored from an ancient fossil. Tirtouga lived in the sea but came up onto the land to search for prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-45', 'Its jaws are terrifyingly powerful. It could eat Omastar and Omanyte whole and not be bothered in the slightest by their shells.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-46', 'They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-48', 'When two Dewpider meet, they display their water bubbles to each other. Then the one with the smaller bubble gets out of the other''s way.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-49', 'It usually passes its time in the water. When its belly is full, it stores its subdued prey in the water bubble on its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-50', 'It will pick up anything it finds on the ground. Sometimes it finds coins, so Murkrow and Meowth will go after it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-51', 'The shell covering its body is as hard as diamond. This Pokémon will do anything it takes to win.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-52', 'The tradition known as Pyukumuku chucking started from the custom of throwing Pyukumuku back into the sea after they wash onshore.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-53', 'This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-55', 'Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-56', 'Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-57', 'It focuses psychic energy into its tail and rides it like it''s surfing. Another name for this Pokémon is "hodad."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-58', 'It''s frequently the cause of power outages, which is why some power plants send out electrical signals that it can''t stand.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-59', 'Delicate equipment can malfunction in areas inhabited by Magneton, which send out mysterious electrical signals.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-60', 'It uses radar to monitor its territory. Intruders are quickly disposed of with a hyper beam.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-61', 'Since it can''t generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-62', 'They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-63', 'While one alone doesn''t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-64', 'While one alone doesn''t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-65', 'It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-66', 'With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-67', 'Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-68', 'The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-69', 'Although it''s called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-70', 'Although it''s alien to this world and a danger here, it''s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-73', 'Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-74', 'It engages its enemies using psychic powers. Each of its three heads fires off psychokinetic energy, tripling its power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-75', 'The rich greenery of the Alola region is hard on Marowak. It controls fire to stay alive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-76', 'It sways its hips to a rhythm all its own. The precise movements of Jynx living in Alola are truly wonderful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-77', 'It tends to move in a pack with others. They cluster in a tight group to sleep in a cave.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-80', 'Its round body is stuffed with souls and expands each time it leads someone away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-81', 'There''s a rumor that if you catch a Drifblim floating on the wind at dusk, you''ll be carried away to the afterlife.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-82', 'It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-83', 'Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-84', 'Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-85', 'Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-86', 'This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-87', 'Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-88', 'This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-89', 'The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-90', 'It controls tremendous psychic power. Most reports of alien sightings are actually just people mistaking Elgyem for an alien.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-91', 'With its psychic powers, it rewrites its opponents'' memories. You, too, may have already had your memories rewritten.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-92', 'Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-93', 'Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-94', 'When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-95', 'Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-96', 'They eat Corsola branches, so Mareanie are hated by craftsmen who work with Corsola branches that have naturally fallen off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-97', 'To attack, this Pokémon sends toxic spikes flying at its enemies. Ones that come close get mown down by the claws on its feet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-98', 'The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can''t evolve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-99', 'Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-100', 'Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn''t seem to care.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-101', 'It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It''s apparently from another world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-102', 'This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-103', 'Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-104', 'Tempered underground under high pressure and heat, its body is harder than any metal.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-105', 'At night, it weeps loudly for its dead mother, but those cries only attract its natural enemy—Mandibuzz.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm11-107', 'It''s proud of its thick horn. In Alola, its biggest rival is Vikavolt, which it''s always fighting with.')
