INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-91', 'It rides on the wind and slips into people''s homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton-filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-93', 'It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-94', 'The weakest of all Dragon-type Pokémon, it''s unable to breathe if its skin dries out, so it sticks to shady places.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-95', 'It has trouble drawing a line between friends and food. It will calmly try to melt and eat even those it gets along well with.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-96', 'An amazingly friendly Pokémon, but if left to itself, loneliness overcomes it, and it oozes gooey tears.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-97', 'It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it will completely destroy its surroundings with its intense breath.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-98', 'It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-99', 'It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-101', 'The eggs laid by Chansey are rich in nutrients and a favorite food of many Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-102', 'Even the most ferocious Pokémon become calm when they eat Blissey''s egg, which is said to be filled with happiness.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-103', 'It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-104', 'If its two tail feathers are standing at attention, it is proof of good health. It soars elegantly in the sky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-105', 'It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-106', 'It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-107', 'Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-108', 'Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-109', 'This amiable Pokémon is easy to train. But when battle is joined, it shows its ferocious side.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-110', 'From its beak, it fires embers at its prey. Once it has caught them, it grills them at high heat before feasting upon them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-111', 'Its favorite foods are Wingull and Pikipek. It attacks with a powerful kick and grasps them firmly in its talons.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-112', 'Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-113', 'This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm2-114', 'It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-1', 'When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-2', 'Its shell is filled with its soft innards. It doesn''t move much because of the risk it might carelessly spill its innards out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-3', 'Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-4', 'During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-5', 'Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-6', 'The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-7', 'Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-8', 'It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-9', 'They are timid and grow uneasy when not in a swarm with others of their kind. The pattern on their backs differs slightly from one to another.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-10', 'While it''s believed that starlight provides it with energy, this Pokémon also loves to eat berries. In the daytime, it curls up in the grass to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-11', 'This powerful Pokémon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies'' bellies, then lifts and throws them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-12', 'It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-13', 'It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokémon is wild tempered.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-14', 'It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-15', 'It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-16', 'This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-18', 'The flame on its tail indicates Charmander''s life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-18a', 'The flame on its tail indicates Charmander''s life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-19', 'It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-22', 'Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-23', 'A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-24', 'Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant''s steel bodies and consume their insides.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-26', 'The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-27', 'It exhales air colder than -58 degrees Fahrenheit. Elderly people in Alola call this Pokémon by an older name—Keokeo.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-28', 'It creates drops of ice in its coat and showers them over its enemies. Anyone who angers it will be frozen stiff in an instant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-29', 'Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-30', 'Its body bristles with sharp spikes. Carelessly trying to touch it could cause fainting from the spikes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-31', 'It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-32', 'Although weak and helpless, this Pokémon is incredibly fertile. They exist in such multitudes, you''ll soon grow tired of seeing them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-33', 'A tale is told of a town that angered Gyarados. Before the sun rose the next day, flames utterly consumed the town, leaving not a trace behind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-34', 'The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry, even when it plays in the water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-35', 'Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-36', 'The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-37', 'The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-38', 'When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-40', 'A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-41', 'It unleashes electric shocks that can reach 100,000 volts. When agitated, it can knock out even an Indian elephant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-42', 'Half of all sudden blackouts are caused by Electabuzz gathering at electric power plants and gobbling up electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-43', 'It pushes the tips of its tails against its foes and then lets loose a high-voltage current. Its foes are burned to a crisp in an instant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-44', 'While one alone doesn''t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-45', 'It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-46', 'With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-47', 'The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-48', 'A poisonous bite reacted with its system, blessing it with the enhanced intellect of a genius. It has full control of its psychic powers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-49', 'It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to build up its counterstrike.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-50', 'In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any Zangoose. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-51', 'It doggedly pursues its prey wherever it goes. However, the chase is abandoned at sunrise.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-52', 'Anyone who dares peer into its body to see its spectral ball of fire will have their spirit stolen away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-53', 'It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-54', 'Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-55', 'It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-56', 'It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-57', 'Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-58', 'It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-59', 'The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-60', 'When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck to dust.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-61', 'Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokémon embodies the grudges of the departed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-62', 'Possessed people controlled by this Pokémon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-65', 'Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging Tackles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-66', 'Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-67', 'From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude. Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-68', 'Because it turns active on nights of the full moon, it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-69', 'Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-70', 'It can discern the physical and emotional states of people, Pokémon, and other natural things from the shape of their aura waves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-71', 'Not only does it perceive auras, but it has also gained the power to control them. It employs them in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-72', 'Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-73', 'While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-74', 'It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-75', 'The more intimidating the opponent it faces, the more this Pokémon''s blood boils. It will attack with no regard for its own safety.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-76', 'Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-77', 'The mud stuck to Mudbray''s hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-78', 'It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-79', 'They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-81', 'With its incisors, it gnaws through doors and infiltrates people''s homes. Then, with a twitch of its whiskers, it steals whatever food it finds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-82', 'It forms a group of Rattata, which it assumes command of. Each group has its own territory, and disputes over food happen often.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-83', 'A Grimer, which had been brought in to solve a problem with garbage, developed over time into this form.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-85', 'It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-86', 'They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-87', 'It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-89', 'Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-90', 'It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-91', 'If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-92', 'The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-94', 'A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-95', 'It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it''s able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-96', 'It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-97', 'It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-98', 'Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-100', 'This is Zygarde''s form at times when it uses its overwhelming power to suppress those who endanger the ecosystem.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-101', 'It lies around all day, becoming active near dusk. At night, it wanders the city in search of loose change.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-102', 'It has a violent temperament. It will attack anything that looks it in the eye. Its sharp claws inflict deep wounds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-103', 'Roughly 20 years ago, it was artificially created, utilizing the latest technology of the time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-104', 'For the purposes of planetary development, Porygon was updated with the most cutting-edge technology available.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-105', 'In order to create a more advanced Pokémon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-105a', 'In order to create a more advanced Pokémon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-106', 'It has a perfect sense of time. Whatever happens, it keeps rhythm by precisely tilting its head in time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-107', 'Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-108', 'They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-109', 'They live in pitch black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-110', 'Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm3-111', 'This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-1', 'A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-2', 'There is a plant bulb on its back. When it absorbs nutrients, the bulb is said to blossom into a large flower.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-3', 'By spreading the broad petals of its flower and catching the sun''s rays, it fills its body with power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-4', 'It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-5', 'Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-6', 'It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-7', 'It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-8', 'Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-9', 'This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-11', 'Coal is the source of Torkoal''s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-12', 'Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-13', 'A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-14', 'This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-15', 'While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-16', 'At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-17', 'This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it''s not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer''s orders with complete nonchalance.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-18', 'It is small but rough and tough. It won''t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-19', 'If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-20', 'It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-21', 'To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-22', 'It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-23', 'It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-24', 'It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-25', 'It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-26', 'It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-27', 'It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It''s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-28', 'A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-30', 'It was discovered when Poké Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-31', 'It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of "The Bomb Ball."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-32', 'The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-33', 'It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-34', 'Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-35', 'This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-36', 'The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-37', 'The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-38', 'It wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-40', 'Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-41', 'A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-42', 'Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-43', 'The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-44', 'It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-45', 'Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-46', 'Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-47', 'A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-48', 'Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-49', 'Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-50', 'Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-51', 'It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-52', 'It changes so it looks like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-54', 'When this legendary Pokémon''s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-55', 'In its true form, it possess a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-56', 'It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm35-57', 'According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-1', 'Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-2', 'Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself when it is in danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-3', 'May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-4', 'Its six eggs use telepathy to communicate among themselves. It is believed to carry plant genes and the genes of other species.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-5', 'It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-6', 'It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day''s desert heat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-7', 'These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-8', 'When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-9', 'Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-10', 'Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-11', 'It can tell how its trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathetic sense lets them run as if one being.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-12', 'The bones it possesses were once its mother''s. Its mother''s regrets have become like a vengeful spirit protecting this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-13', 'Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-14', 'The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years—or whenever it becomes really angry.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-15', 'Large numbers of these Pokémon make their home at the seaside. At night, a strange red glow radiates from the center of their bodies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-16', 'Its shining core is thought to receive and transmit enigmatic signals. It has been known to cause headaches in those who approach it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-17', 'Although weak and helpless, this Pokémon is incredibly fertile. They exist in such multitudes, you''ll soon grow tired of seeing them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-19', 'It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-20', 'Although its legs are short, its rugged hooves prevent it from slipping, even on icy ground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-21', 'A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice dating back 10,000 years. This Pokémon has been around a long, long, long time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-22', 'It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike even moving prey from more than 300 feet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-23', 'It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-24', 'No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-25', 'It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-26', 'A tough Pokémon that is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn''t popular.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-27', 'Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-28', 'It is said to have slept in a glacier for thousands of years. Its body can''t be melted, even by magma.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-29', 'For the most part, it makes its home along the seashore. Its color and form differ according to its habitat and the quality of its food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-30', 'A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-31', 'It only evolves to this form in the Alola region. According to researchers, its diet is one of the causes of this change.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-32', 'Its body is a magnetic stone. Iron sand attaches firmly to the portions of its body that are particularly magnetic.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-33', 'Its preferred food is dravite. After it has eaten this mineral, crystals form inside the Pokémon, rising to the surface of part of its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-35', 'It glides using its cape-like membrane. Electrical energy scatters from it, shocking its friends and foes alike.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-36', 'Should a strange light be seen flickering in an abandoned building, Gastly is lurking there.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-37', 'It strikes at humans from total darkness. Those licked by its cold tongue grow weaker with each passing day until they die.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-38', 'Should you feel yourself attacked by a sudden chill, it is evidence of an approaching Gengar. There is no escaping it. Give up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-39', 'It will use any means necessary to frighten people and absorb their life energy. It practices constantly to hone its skill in causing fear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-40', 'It appears as if from nowhere—muttering incantations, placing curses, and giving people terrifying visions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-41', 'It bounces constantly, using its tail like a spring. The shock of bouncing keeps its heart beating.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-42', 'It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes'' minds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-43', 'It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-44', 'The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-45', 'Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-46', 'It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-47', 'For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-48', 'Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it''s best suited to veteran Trainers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-50', 'It can spontaneously become enraged. Everyone near it clears out as it rampages and the resulting loneliness makes it angrier still.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-51', 'It has been known to become so angry that it dies as a result. Its face looks peaceful in death, however.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-52', 'When it thinks of its deceased mother, it weeps loudly. Mandibuzz that hear its cries will attack it from the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-53', 'Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-54', 'It has strong regenerative capabilities. Even if parts of it are bitten off by fish Pokémon, it will return to normal within a few hours.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-55', 'Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-56', 'This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-58', 'Around dawn, its ominous howl echoes through the area to announce that this is its territory.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-59', 'Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-60', 'They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-61', 'The two heads do not get along. Whichever head eats more than the other gets to be the leader.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-62', 'The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-64', 'It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-65', 'It usually lives deep in mountains. However, hunger may drive it to eat railroad tracks and cars.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-66', 'It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory by bashing one another with their steel bodies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-67', 'It claims an entire mountain as its own. The more wounds it has, the more it has battled, so don''t take it lightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-68', 'Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-69', 'Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-71', 'It hugely inflates its stomach and sings a mysterious melody. If you hear this melody, you''ll become sleepy right away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-72', 'It sheds its fine fur when the seasons change. The fur is gathered and spun into a luxurious yarn.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-73', 'Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-75', 'It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-76', 'It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-77', 'When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-78', 'Its milk is high in calories and packed with nutrients. Therefore, if you drink too much of it, you may wind up with a body like Miltank''s.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-79', 'For some reason, it likes to land on people''s heads softly and act like it''s a hat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-80', 'It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic humming makes you feel like you''re in a dream.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-81', 'They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-82', 'They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-83', 'The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-84', 'It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-84a', 'It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-85', 'Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-86', 'Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-87', 'They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-88', 'With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm4-89', 'The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-1', 'Its six eggs use telepathy to communicate among themselves. It is believed to carry plant genes and the genes of other species.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-2', 'If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-3', 'This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-4', 'Roselia that drink nutritionally rich springwater are said to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-5', 'With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-6', 'It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-7', 'It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-8', 'It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-9', 'Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-10', 'It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-11', 'If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun''s rays with its whole body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-12', 'It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-14', 'Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-15', 'The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-16', 'It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-17', 'It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-18', 'When angered, it spouts brilliant fire from all over its body. It doesn''t calm down until its opponent has burned to ash.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-19', 'From its arm, it launches fireballs hotter than 3,500 degrees Fahrenheit. Its arm starts to melt when it fires a whole barrage.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-20', 'The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.')
