INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-47', 'Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-48', 'Luxray''s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it''s scouting for danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-49', 'A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-50', 'Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-51', 'If for some reason its body bursts, its soul spills out with a screaming sound.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-52', 'Even while under careful observation, large flocks of Drifblim flying at dusk will inexplicably disappear from view.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-53', 'It was bound to a fissure in an Odd Keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-54', 'It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-55', 'It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-56', 'Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-57', 'Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-58', 'It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-59', 'Those who sleep holding Cresselia''s feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-60', 'Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-61', 'There''s something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokémon may come from another world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-62', 'Said to live in another world, this Pokémon devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of night over the brightness of day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-64', 'In rock layers where Cranidos fossils are found, the fossilized trunks of trees snapped in two are also often found.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-65', 'Records exist of a revived fossil that evolved into Rampardos. It proceeded to escape and then destroy a skyscraper with a headbutt.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-66', 'It''s tough enough to run right through the night, and it''s also a hard worker, but it''s still just a youngster.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-67', 'They can detect the species of a living being—and its emotions—from over half a mile away. They control auras and hunt their prey in packs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-68', 'It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-69', 'It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-70', 'They battle with hard berries for weapons. Their techniques are passed from the boss to the group, generation upon generation.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-71', 'Seen as a symbol of bad luck, it''s generally disliked. Yet it gives presents—objects that sparkle or shine—to Trainers it''s close to.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-72', 'If its Murkrow cronies fail to catch food for it, or if it feels they have betrayed it, it will hunt them down wherever they are and punish them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-73', 'It uses its claws to poke holes in eggs so it can slurp out the insides. Breeders consider it a scourge and will drive it away or eradicate it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-74', 'They dwell in cold places. This Pokémon''s main food source in Alola is Vulpix and Sandshrew, which they carefully divide among their group.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-75', 'It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-76', 'It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-77', 'It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-78', 'Its golden hairs function as sensors. It pokes them out of its burrow to monitor its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-79', 'These Pokémon are cherished in the Alola region, where they are thought to be feminine deities of the land incarnate.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-80', 'It sends out electromagnetic waves, which let it float through the air. Touching it while it''s eating electricity will give you a full-body shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-81', 'It sends out electromagnetic waves, which let it float through the air. Touching it while it''s eating electricity will give you a full-body shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-82', 'It has about three times the electrical power of Magnemite. For some reason, outbreaks of this Pokémon happen when lots of sunspots appear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-83', 'As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin, while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-84', 'This Pokémon lived in primeval jungles. Few enemies would have been willing to square off against its heavily armored face, so it''s thought.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-85', 'It lived in the same environments as Rampardos. Their fossils have been found together—seemingly from after they''d fought to the finish.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-86', 'Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-87', 'Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-88', 'Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-89', 'This Pokémon is said to be a male evolution of Cosmog. At the activation of its third eye, it departs for another world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-91', 'This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-92', 'It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-93', 'Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-94', 'This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-95', 'Alola is the best environment for this Pokémon. Local people take pride in its appearance, saying this is how Exeggutor ought to look.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-96', 'It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-97', 'It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-98', 'Shiny objects are its passion. It can be found in its cave, scarcely moving, its gaze fixed on the jewels it''s amassed or Carbink it has caught.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-99', 'The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-102', 'Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-103', 'Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-104', 'Current studies show it can evolve into an incredible eight different species of Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-105', 'Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-106', 'When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-107', 'The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-108', 'When it''s happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm5-109', 'To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.')
