INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm8-165', 'By bending its beak, it can produce a variety of calls and brand itself a noisy nuisance for its neighbors.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm8-166', 'Within its beak, its internal gas ignites, explosively launching seeds with enough power to pulverize boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-2', 'Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-3', 'Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-4', 'Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself when it is in danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-5', 'It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-6', 'Whether it''s due to a lack of moisture or a lack of nutrients, in Alola the mushrooms on Paras don''t grow up quite right.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-7', 'The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-8', 'Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-9', 'It gets into territorial disputes with Vikavolt. For some reason, it apparently gets along well with Heracross in Alola.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-10', 'The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-11', 'The flame on its tail indicates Charmander''s life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-12', 'The flame on its tail indicates Charmander''s life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-13', 'It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-14', 'When expelling a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-15', 'Its beautiful tails have made it very popular. However, if it''s not brushed diligently, it will be a mass of tangles before you know it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-16', 'It is vindictive and relentless by nature. Those who cross it even once will be cursed for a thousand years, along with their descendants.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-17', 'As a newborn, it can barely stand. However, through galloping, its legs are made tougher and faster.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-18', 'Very competitive, this Pokémon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-19', 'It is said to be the legendary bird Pokémon of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flare of flames.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-20', 'It doesn''t allow its emotions to be easily seen. Earning its trust takes time. It prefers solitude.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-21', 'It boasts powerful front legs. With a single punch, it can bend an iron bar right over.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-22', 'It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-23', 'It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-24', 'When tapped, this Pokémon will pull in its head, but its tail will still stick out a little bit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-25', 'It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-26', 'Using psychokinesis gives it a headache, so it normally passes the time spacing out and doing as little as possible.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-27', 'Even fast-swimming fish Pokémon can be disabled by Golduck. It brings them to a standstill and seizes them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-28', 'In many places, there are folktales of stardust falling into the ocean and becoming Staryu.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-29', 'In the distant past, they were fairly strong, but they have become gradually weaker over time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-30', 'It fires hyper beams in all directions, burning the surrounding area to ash. There are some regions where it''s called "the deity of destruction."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-31', 'It likes swimming around with people on its back. In the Alola region, it''s an important means of transportation over water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-32', 'A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-34', 'If you mistake it for a rock and step on it, it will headbutt you in anger. In addition to the pain, it will also zap you with a shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-35', 'If you mistake it for a rock and step on it, it will headbutt you in anger. In addition to the pain, it will also zap you with a shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-36', 'When two Graveler fight each other, it fills the surroundings with flashes of light and sound. People call it the "fireworks of the earth."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-37', 'It''s grumpy and stubborn. If you upset it, it discharges electricity from the surface of its body and growls with a voice like thunder.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-38', 'It was discovered when Poké Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-39', 'It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of "The Bomb Ball."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-40', 'A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-41', 'It stores lots of air in its soft fur, allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-42', 'If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-44', 'Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-45', 'They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-46', 'It grills berries and bug Pokémon with electric shocks and makes a meal of them. It usually nests in the holes gouged in trees by Pikipek.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-47', 'They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-48', 'When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-49', 'The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-50', 'It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-51', 'It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-52', 'It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they''ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-54', 'Although small, its venomous barbs render this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-55', 'The female has a gentle temperament. It emits ultrasonic cries that have the power to befuddle foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-56', 'It uses its scaly, rugged body to seal the entrance of its nest and protect its young from predators.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-57', 'It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-58', 'It raises its big ears to check its surroundings. If it senses anything, it attacks immediately.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-59', 'It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn, as it contains venom.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-60', 'It drifts through the sea searching for prey. Its poisonous tentacles break off sometimes, but after a while, they grow back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-61', 'It fires off ultrasonic waves from its red orbs to weaken its prey, and then it wraps them up in its 80 tentacles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-62', 'It was born from sludge on the ocean floor. In a sterile environment, the germs within its body can''t multiply, and it dies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-63', 'Their food sources have decreased, and their numbers have declined sharply. Sludge ponds are being built to prevent their extinction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-64', 'Its custom is to mourn its lost companions. Mounds of dirt by the side of the road mark the graves of the Marowak.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-65', 'Its sparkling core is called "the gem of the sea." This core can be made into high-priced accessories that are traded in secret.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-66', 'Its pantomime skills are wonderful. You may become enraptured while watching it, but next thing you know, Mr. Mime has made a real wall.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-68', 'It sways its hips to a rhythm all its own. The precise movements of Jynx living in Alola are truly wonderful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-69', 'In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It''s said to be a Pokémon from another world, but no specific details are known.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-70', 'There''s something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokémon may come from another world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-71', 'The smallest of things could cause it to lose its temper. Because it doesn''t hold in its stress, this Pokémon can live a long time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-72', 'It will never forgive opponents who have angered it. Even after it has beaten them down until they can''t move, it never ever forgives.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-73', 'The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-74', 'The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-75', 'Omanyte lived in the seas of antiquity. Its fossils have been found bearing bite marks from Archeops, so apparently Archeops preyed on it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-76', 'Its heavy shell is thought to be the reason this ancient Pokémon died out. It''s apparently a distant ancestor of Octillery.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-77', 'This Pokémon thrived 300 million years ago. It''s said that living specimens can still be seen in a certain region—a rare sight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-78', 'Its body had begun to change so it could function on land. But it didn''t adapt in time and went extinct.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-79', 'Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-80', 'Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-81', 'There''s no point to the leaf in its mouth, aside from an effort to look cool. It''s mischievous, so it''s not well suited to inexperienced Trainers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-83', 'The crystals on Grimer''s body are lumps of toxins. If one falls off, lethal poisons leak out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-84', 'While it''s unexpectedly quiet and friendly, if it''s not fed any trash for a while, it will smash its Trainer''s furnishings and eat up the fragments.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-85', 'If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-86', 'It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-87', 'It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-88', 'Although it''s said to bring disaster, in actuality, this Pokémon possesses a calm disposition and warns people of any crises that loom.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-89', 'It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-90', 'To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-91', 'Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-92', 'It can''t fly yet and must wait until its wings have developed more. Since it''s still at a playful age, it hops around friskily.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-93', 'It circles in the sky, keeping a keen eye out for Pokémon in a weakened state. Its choicest food is Cubone.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-94', 'From the slight twitches of its bamboo leaf, it deduces its opponent''s movements. It''s eager to tussle but kindhearted toward its companions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-95', 'When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-98', 'Its metal body is sturdy, but it does rust rather easily. So on rainy days, this Pokémon prefers to stay put in its nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-99', 'It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-100', 'Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-101', 'Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-102', 'It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-103', 'They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-104', 'Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-105', 'Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-107', 'If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person''s arm and drains that person''s life energy completely.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-108', 'The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-109', 'Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-110', 'It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-111', 'It creates drops of ice in its coat and showers them over its enemies. Anyone who angers it will be frozen stiff in an instant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-112', 'Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-114', 'As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-115', 'Exeggutor is the pride of the Alolan people. Its image is carved into historical buildings and murals.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-116', 'It''s still weak, so it lurks on the floor of bodies of water, eating whatever food sinks down and living a quiet life.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-117', 'It''s still weak, so it lurks on the floor of bodies of water, eating whatever food sinks down and living a quiet life.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-118', 'Lakes where Dragonair live are filled with offerings from people, because they believe this Pokémon is able to control the weather.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-119', 'It flies over raging seas as if they were nothing. Observing this, a ship''s captain dubbed this Pokémon "the sea incarnate."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-121', 'A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-122', 'A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-123', 'The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute to its nest over 60 miles away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-124', 'When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-125', 'When visiting a junkyard, you may catch sight of it having an intense fight with Murkrow over shiny objects.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-126', 'Although the jewel on its forehead appears to be a different color than those of Alolan Persian, it''s mostly made of the same material.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-127', 'The plant stalk it holds is its weapon. The stalk is used like a sword to cut all sorts of things.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-128', 'Kangaskhan protects its child by keeping it in its pouch. It has zero forgiveness for those who harm its child and will beat them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-129', 'They live in groups. The one with the longest, thickest, and most-scarred horns is the boss of the herd.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-130', 'Restored from DNA found in amber, this Pokémon exhibited ferocity that was greater than expected. Some casualties resulted.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-131', 'It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sm9-132', 'Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV1', 'While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV2', 'This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV3', 'A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV4', 'This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV5', 'One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV6', 'From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV7', 'When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the air temperature to unbearably high levels.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV8', 'It exhales air colder than -58 degrees Fahrenheit. Elderly people in Alola call this Pokémon by an older name—Keokeo.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV9', 'When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV10', 'This carefree Pokémon has an easygoing nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV11', 'It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV12', 'Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute''s time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV13', 'Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV14', 'It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a power plant, so people think it energizes itself with electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV15', 'In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any Zangoose. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV16', 'It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV17', 'It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent''s will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV18', 'It lures prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV19', 'This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV20', 'To avoid attack, it mimics a tree. It will run off if splashed with water, which it hates.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV21', 'It''s tough enough to run right through the night, and it''s also a hard worker, but it''s still just a youngster.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV22', 'They can detect the species of a living being—and its emotions—from over half a mile away. They control auras and hunt their prey in packs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV23', 'This Pokémon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer''s side.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV24', 'A mysterious life-form called an Ultra Beast. Witnesses saw it pulverize a dump truck with a single punch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV25', 'It changes so it looks like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV26', 'A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating constantly, but for some reason its droppings have never been found.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV27', 'It sends out electromagnetic waves, which let it float through the air. Touching it while it''s eating electricity will give you a full-body shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV28', 'It has about three times the electrical power of Magnemite. For some reason, outbreaks of this Pokémon happen when lots of sunspots appear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV29', 'As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin, while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV30', 'Its cells are all magnets. It uses magnetism to communicate with others of its kind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV31', 'When two Beldum link together, their psychic power is doubled. Their intelligence, however, remains unchanged.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV32', 'One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV33', 'One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower with one stroke of its blade.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV34', 'If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV35', 'The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV36', 'A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV37', 'On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV38', 'It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV39', 'Shiny objects are its passion. It can be found in its cave, scarcely moving, its gaze fixed on the jewels it''s amassed or Carbink it has caught.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV40', 'The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV41', 'Current studies show it can evolve into an incredible eight different species of Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV42', 'It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV43', 'They live in pitch black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV44', 'Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('sma-SV45', 'The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM01', 'This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM02', 'While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM03', 'This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It''s famous for being a hard worker.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM04', 'A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM06', 'It''s considered to be a good Pokémon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM07', 'It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses holes for food storage and for nesting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM08', 'While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM09', 'The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM10', 'It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM11', 'It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder''s shell is no match for it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM12', 'They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM13', 'Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM15', 'This is Zygarde''s form at times when it uses its overwhelming power to suppress those who endanger the ecosystem.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM18', 'Fleeing a volcanic eruption, it settled on a snowy mountain. As it races through the snowfields, it sends up a spray of snow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM19', 'This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Its elegant, attractive dance will send the minds and hearts of its enemies to another world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM20', 'It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM21', 'It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('smp-SM22', 'This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.')
