INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-52', 'If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-54', 'When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won''t be able to resist weeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-55', 'When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won''t be able to resist weeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-56', 'A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-57', 'A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-58', 'It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-59', 'It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-60', 'It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-61', 'This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-62', 'It''s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it''s battling midfight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-63', 'It eats snow that piles up on the ground. The more snow it eats, the bigger and more impressive the spikes on its back grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-64', 'It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-65', 'Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-66', 'Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-67', 'On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-68', 'Its antennae, which evolved from a fin, have both positive and negative charges flowing through them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-69', 'This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-70', 'Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It''s soaking up static electricity because it can''t produce a charge on its own.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-71', 'It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-73', 'This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-74', 'This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-75', 'This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-76', 'This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-77', 'It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-78', 'As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It''s also generating electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-81', 'This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-82', 'Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-83', 'Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-84', 'Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-85', 'On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar''s doing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-87', 'It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it''s eating a good dream, and black when it''s eating a nightmare.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-88', 'It drowses and dreams all the time. It''s best to leave it be if it''s just woken up, as it''s a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-89', 'This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-90', 'This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-92', 'If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-93', 'A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-94', 'The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-95', 'Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-96', 'It can remember only one thing at a time. Once it starts rushing, it forgets why it started.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-97', 'Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-98', 'Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-99', 'It relies on its carapace to deflect incoming attacks and throw its enemy off balance. As soon as that happens, it drives its drill into the foe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-100', 'If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it''s a Sudowoodo, not a tree. It hides from the rain.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-101', 'It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-102', 'It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-103', 'This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-105', 'Loads weighing up to 50 times as much as its own body weight pose no issue for this Pokémon. It''s skilled at making use of mud.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-106', 'Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale''s legs sets harder than stone. It''s so hard that it allows this Pokémon to scrap a truck with a single kick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-107', 'It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-108', 'As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-109', 'Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-110', 'When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-111', 'It''s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-112', 'It''s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-113', 'A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-114', 'It stands in grasslands, watching the sun''s descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-117', 'Thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon, it moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-118', 'This very aggressive Pokémon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-119', 'It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-121', 'It attacks using the claws on its tail. Once locked in its grip, its prey is unable to move as this Pokémon''s poison seeps in.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-122', 'It''s so vicious that it''s called the Sand Demon. Yet when confronted by Hippowdon, Drapion keeps a low profile and will never pick a fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-123', 'It makes frightening noises with its poison-filled cheek sacs. When opponents flinch, Croagunk hits them with a poison jab.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-124', 'It bounces toward opponents and gouges them with poisonous claws. No more than a scratch is needed to knock out its adversaries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-125', 'Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-126', 'It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-127', 'Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokémon''s body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-128', 'What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-129', 'It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-130', 'It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn''t very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-131', 'This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-132', 'Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-133', 'A pack of these Pokémon forms to serve a Bisharp boss. Each Pawniard trains diligently, dreaming of one day taking the lead.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-134', 'Violent conflicts erupt between Bisharp and Fraxure over places where sharpening stones can be found.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-135', 'This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-136', 'If a job requires serious strength, this Pokémon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning a vibrant green color.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-137', 'These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-140', 'It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-143', 'It begins to hoot at the same time every day. Some Trainers use them in place of clocks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-144', 'When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-145', 'The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-146', 'The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-147', 'Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won''t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-148', 'It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-149', 'The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-150', 'It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-151', 'Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-152', 'If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won''t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-153', 'Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh1-154', 'Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-2', 'An enigmatic Pokémon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poké Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-3', 'The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn. When irritated, this Pokémon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-4', 'The large, wickedly sharp scythes on its forearms are truly fearsome weapons. Prey''s attempts to flee are unfailingly thwarted by this Pokémon''s nimble motions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-5', 'The large, wickedly sharp scythes on its forearms are truly fearsome weapons. Prey''s attempts to flee are unfailingly thwarted by this Pokémon''s nimble motions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-6', 'Its frail wings are so thin that one can see clear through them. However, during flight these wings exhibit the power to churn air with force enough to launch a house skyward.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-7', 'This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-8', 'This Pokémon has an unparalleled horn. Heracross itself demonstrates tremendous power—it''s capable of throwing several people trained in the traditional arts of war at once.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-9', 'When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-10', 'It uses its cutlass-like arms to produce sound, the melody of which varies from individual to individual. It is a worthwhile endeavor to seek out one''s favorite tunes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-11', 'The members of the trio spend all their time together. Each one has a slightly different taste in nectar.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-12', 'It skillfully commands its grubs in battles with its enemies. The grubs are willing to risk their lives to defend Vespiquen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-13', 'Cells similar to those of plants have been found in its fur. Its hard tail can fell a large tree with one stroke, and the tail''s sharpness exceeds even that of a sword crafted by a master.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-14', 'When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-15', 'The leaves on its head are highly valued for medicinal purposes. Dry the leaves in the sun, boil them, and then drink the bitter decoction for remarkably effective relief from fatigue.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-16', 'I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-19', 'Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. It has mastered the art of deftly launching dagger-sharp feathers from those same wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-20', 'Regularly basks in sunlight to gather power—presumably due to the frigid climate. Nonetheless, the edges of the blade quills set into its wings are keen as ever.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-21', 'These Pokémon live in herds out in the grassland. Newborn foals lack their fiery manes, which will develop about an hour after birth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-22', 'This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-23', 'Hails from the Johto region. Though usually curled into a ball due to its timid disposition, it harbors tremendous firepower.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-24', 'This creature''s fur is most mysterious—it is wholly impervious to the burning touch of flame. Should Quilava turn its back to you, take heed! Such a posture indicates a forthcoming attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-27', 'Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-28', 'Suffers perpetual headaches. If the agony grows too great, Psyduck''s latent power erupts, contrary to Psyduck''s intent. Ergo, I am exploring ways to ease the pain.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-29', 'This Pokémon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs, putting its graceful swimming skills on display.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-31', 'Swinub excels at sniffing out mushrooms buried beneath grass or snow. Since ancient times, the people of Hisui have often relied upon this skill.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-32', 'If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-33', 'This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a while, it was thought to have gone extinct.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-34', 'This calm and gentle Pokémon swims gracefully through the sea. After building speed, it can leap out of the water. It is often misidentified as a bird Pokémon due to this behavior.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-35', 'Makes its home in swamps with murky water. The poor visibility hides this Pokémon from predators, and the slime on its body makes grasping it difficult.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-36', 'It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything—if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-37', 'With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as −328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-38', 'Glaceon is able to lower its body temperature very quickly. It freezes the atmosphere, creating diamond dust that glitters like gems while it flutters and dances around.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-41', 'This Pokémon from the Unova region uses the shell on its belly as a weapon to cut down its foes. Thus, I''ve conferred upon this shell the name “scalchop.”.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-42', 'Its exquisite double-scalchop technique is likely the result of daily training, and it can send even masters of the blade fleeing in defeat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-43', 'Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor—this one is gentle—I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-44', 'Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui''s rivers is Basculegion''s equal.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-45', 'When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-46', 'It appears and vanishes with a ninja''s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-47', 'Lives on mountains blanketed in perennial snow. It freezes water vapor in the air to make the ice helmet that it dons for defense.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-48', 'The armor of ice covering its lower jaw puts steel to shame and can shatter rocks with ease. This Pokémon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-51', 'This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. It''s said that removing the rings on Regieleki''s body will unleash the Pokémon''s latent power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-52', 'Said to purify lost, forsaken souls with its flames and guide them to the afterlife. I believe its form has been influenced by the energy of the sacred mountain towering at Hisui''s center.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-55', 'This ovate creature is frequently mistaken for a moving egg when encountered out in the fields or in the mountains. Its guileless smile soothes the soul.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-56', 'They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-57', 'These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they''ve hardly been seen at all.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-58', 'It conceals itself in darkness, sending chills up travelers'' spines with its childlike weeping. As it observes the frightened travelers with glee, the red orbs upon its chest let offan eerie light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-59', 'Its muttered curses can cause awful headaches or terrifying visions that torment others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-60', 'Tends to prefer people with a chipper disposition to those who are gloomy, but it has shown no discrimination with regard to age or gender. Needs more research.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-61', 'If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-62', 'True to its honorable-warrior image, it uses the blades on its elbows only in defense of something or someone.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-63', 'Said to lure away young children and carry them off to the afterlife. Some whisper that Drifloon are formed of reincarnated human souls, but these rumors are as yet unconfirmed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-64', 'Some say this Pokémon is a collection of souls burdened with regrets, silently drifting through the dusk.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-65', 'It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-66', 'It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake''s surface.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-67', 'It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-68', 'It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-69', 'The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-70', 'They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-71', 'Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-74', 'Though it pretends to be a tree, it fails to fool even children. To the touch, its body feels more like rock than tree bark. Sudowoodo''s extreme aversion to water merits special note.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-75', 'Every bit of Regirock''s body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks rocks to itself to repair what''s been lost.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-76', 'Its hard skull is its distinguishing feature. It snapped trees by headbutting them, and then it fed on their ripe berries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-77', 'This ancient Pokémon used headbutts skillfully. Its brain was really small, so some theories suggest that its stupidity led to its extinction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-79', 'Though large and languid, Hippopotas is difficult to detect due to its tendency to burrow into and lurk beneath the soil. When agitated or excited, it expels sand from its nostrils.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-80', 'Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-81', 'It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-82', 'The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye''s feathers insulates the Pokémon against Hisui''s extreme cold. This is firm proof that evolution can be influenced by environment.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-85', 'A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one''s only recourse is to flee.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-86', 'A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one''s only recourse is to flee.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-88', 'Fishers detest this troublesome Pokémon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-89', 'Fishers detest this troublesome Pokémon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-90', 'Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname “sea fiend.” It slurps up poison to nourish itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-91', 'Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname “sea fiend.” It slurps up poison to nourish itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-92', 'Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in Sneasel''s grasp.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-93', 'Because of Sneasler''s virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-95', 'It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-96', 'It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-97', 'Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-100', 'Hard of heart and deft of blade, this rare form of Samurott is a product of the Pokémon''s evolution in the region of Hisui. Its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-103', 'Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-104', 'It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-105', 'A bizarre Pokémon with but a single eye embedded in an iron sphere. I suspect this creature levitates due to the magnetism it emits from its arms, which resemble horseshoe-shaped magnets.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-106', 'This Pokémon is three Magnemite that have linked together. Magneton sends out powerful radio waves to study its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-107', 'Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it''s being controlled by some mysterious being.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-108', 'Registeel''s body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-109', 'Although its fossils can be found in layers of primeval rock, nothing but its face has ever been discovered.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-110', 'This Pokémon is from roughly 100 million years ago. Its terrifyingly tough face is harder than steel.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-111', 'Floats using a mysterious energy. The pattern engraved upon its back is held as sacred and can sometimes be found in imagery from ancient cemeteries and other such timeworn places.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-112', 'Some believe it to be a deity that summons rain clouds. When angered, it lets out a warning cry that rings out like the tolling of a bell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-115', 'It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-116', 'It''s accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions, ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-118', 'An academic theory proposes that Regidrago''s arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokémon. The theory remains unproven.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-119', 'It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-120', 'It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-121', 'Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-122', 'It licks its paws because of the sweet honey that has soaked into them. It is cunning, stealing into the nests of Combee and taking for itself the honey that the Combee have amassed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-123', 'When the cold season arrives in Hisui, this Pokémon will wander fields and mountains alike in search of its favorite berries. Ursaring''s hunger during this time makes it a ferocious danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-124', 'I believe it was Hisui''s swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-125', 'Its strangely shaped antlers have the power to bewitch those who see them. Medicine made by grinding up the black orbs from fallen antlers is an effective treatment for insomnia.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-126', 'Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it''s been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-127', 'Bewitches humans with its helical tail and piercing gaze. Its hidden claws are quite sharp as well, making this Pokémon an exceedingly tricky opponent if antagonized.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-128', 'To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-129', 'A versatile performer skilled in the imitation of human speech. It is said that older, more experienced Chatot can even understand the meaning of the words they mimic.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-130', 'There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-131', 'Its chick-like looks belie its hotheadedness. It challenges its parents at every opportunity, desperate to prove its strength.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10-132', 'Screaming a bloodcurdling battle cry, this huge and ferocious bird Pokémon goes out on the hunt. It blasts lakes with shock waves, then scoops up any prey that float to the water''s surface.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG01', 'The Pokémon is known to bring blizzards. A shake of its massive body is enough to cause whiteout conditions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG02', 'It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG03', 'It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life forms can survive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG04', 'It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG05', 'To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG06', 'The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG07', 'The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG08', 'A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one''s only recourse is to flee.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG09', 'It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG10', 'It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG11', 'Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh10tg-TG12', 'It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-1', 'If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-2', 'Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-3', 'It has the world''s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-4', 'The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-5', 'The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-6', 'It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-7', 'It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-8', 'It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey''s fluids.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-9', 'It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-10', 'Tends to be drawn to bonfires on dark nights. Difficult to chase away from settlements because of the way it scatters highlyntoxic scales.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-11', 'If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-12', 'It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-13', 'A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe''s mind and take preemptive action.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-14', 'Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-15', 'After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-16', 'After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit''s rebirth as this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-17', 'People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokémon it shares its woods with, it''s kind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-18', 'A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn''t.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-19', 'It barely moves, but it''s still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-20', 'It''s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-21', 'Its body is made of magma. If it doesn''t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-22', 'Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-23', 'It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-24', 'The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokémon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-25', 'This Pokémon appears just before someone passes away, so it''s feared as an emissary of death.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-26', 'This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-28', 'This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-29', 'The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn''t use it on its prey. This Pokémon prefers to eat raw meat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-30', 'For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon''s innards showing through the skin.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-31', 'Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl''s has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-32', 'At nightfall, these Pokémon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-33', 'Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don''t bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-34', 'It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-35', 'Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-36', 'It''s the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-37', 'With the arrival of a storm at sea, this Pokémon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet, a fierce battle ensues.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-38', 'Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola''s branches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-39', 'There''s speculation that its appearance is determined by what it eats, but the truthnremains elusive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-40', 'It lures in prey with its shining tail fins. It stays near the surface during the day and moves to the depths when night falls.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-41', 'They traverse the deep waters as if crawling over the seafloor. The fantastic lights of its fins shine like stars in the night sky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-42', 'One is likely to encounter this Pokémon while out in the snow. There are stories of Snover appearing in human settlements butndoing no harm—rather, they bond with the children.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-43', 'If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-44', 'Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor—this one is gentle—I have categorizednit as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-45', 'Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other speciesnthroughout all Hisui''s rivers is Basculegion''s equal.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-46', 'They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-47', 'Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-50', 'It''s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it''s battling midfight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-51', 'Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It''s also a belligerent Pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-52', 'Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-53', 'Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-54', 'It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-55', 'It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-59', 'One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-60', 'These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-61', 'They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-62', 'It can be found in quiet mountain areas on a full moon''s night. Its dancing and its tiny, faintly glowing wings confer upon it anlovely fairylike quality.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-63', 'A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-64', 'Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-65', 'This frightful, malevolent spirit can glide through walls, appearing wherever it likes. According to rumor, victims ofna Haunter''s lick will wither to death day by day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-66', 'On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar''s doing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-67', 'The behavior of this clown-like Pokémon reminds one of pantomime. It creates invisible walls using a force emittednfrom its fingertips.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-68', 'Its strange cries sound like human language. There are some musicians who compose songs for Jynx to sing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-69', 'It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-70', 'This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it''s believed that Sableye will steal people''s spirits away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-71', 'It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-72', 'There''s a proverb that says, “Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk.”')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-73', 'Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-74', 'Those who sleep holding Cresselia''s feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-75', 'A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takesnon the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-76', 'With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemesesnwith a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark''s own body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-77', 'It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-78', 'Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar''s control.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-79', 'Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won''t wither once they''re attached to a Comfey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-80', 'It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-81', 'It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn''t use its sense of sight. Spectrier''s kicks are said to separate soul from body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-83', 'They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result ofnvolcanic activity in its habitat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-84', 'Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on andeceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-85', 'Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-86', 'Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it''s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-87', 'A sturdy creature boasting a robust physique and boundless stamina. Loves training above all else and voluntarily assists withntasks such as construction and clearing land.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-88', 'It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-89', 'Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-90', 'It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-91', 'It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-94', 'Though it pretends to be a tree, it fails to fool even children. To the touch, its body feels more like rock than tree bark. Sudowoodo''s extreme aversion to water merits special note.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-95', 'It flies straight at its target''s face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-96', 'Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-97', 'There''s a rumor of a traditional recipe for stew that Trainers can use to raise strong Makuhita.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-98', 'Hariyama that are big and fat aren''t necessarily strong. There are some small ones that move nimbly and use moves skillfully.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-99', 'It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-100', 'Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe''s next move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-101', 'Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-102', 'Its search for food sometimes leads it onto land, where it leaves behind a sticky trail of slime as it passes through.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-103', 'In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-104', 'When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-105', 'From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-106', 'After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-107', 'Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-108', 'When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all out by firing high-energy beams from the gems embedded in its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-109', 'This Pokémon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-110', 'Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass''s orders are absolute.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-111', 'It stands in grasslands, watching the sun''s descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-112', 'Although the poison from its fangs isn''t that strong, it''s potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-113', 'It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-114', 'It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow''s presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-115', 'Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-116', 'Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It''s Zangoose''s archrival.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-117', 'Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokémon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-120', 'On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which everynone of a village''s inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-121', 'It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-122', 'It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-123', 'Because of Sneasler''s virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozennhighlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-124', 'It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-125', 'It appears in ancient ruins. The pattern on its body doesn''t come from any culture in the Galar region, so it remains shrouded in mystery.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-126', 'Some believe that its bell-like cry opens holes to another world. It has been revered as a deity since ancient times.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-127', 'Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-128', 'Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-132', 'Goomy hides away in the shade of trees, where it''s nice and humid. If the slime coating its body dries out, the Pokémonninstantly becomes lethargic.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-133', 'A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting withnthe iron in Hisui''s water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-134', 'Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy—it will fume andnrun riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-138', 'If this Pokémon''s sticky saliva gets on you and you don''t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won''t go away, either.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-139', 'Lickilicky''s strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky''s tongue can stretch so far.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-140', 'State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be created via computer programming.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-141', 'This is a Porygon that was updated with special data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about many different subjects all on its own.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-142', 'Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z''s behavior.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-143', 'It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-144', 'This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand. Ancient writings describe this Pokémon as a one-armed oddity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-145', 'It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that''s proof it really likes you.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-148', 'These Pokémon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-149', 'It remains asleep from birth to death as a result of the sedative properties of the leaves that form its diet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-150', 'Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11-151', 'It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn''t notice the loss.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG01', 'Mushroom-lacking specimens of this Pokémon lie unmoving in the forest, lending credence to the hypothesis that the large mushroom is in control of Parasect''s actions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG02', 'After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG03', 'It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG04', 'This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG05', 'Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG06', 'Possesses potential victims'' shadows in an effort to steal away the victims'' lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG07', 'Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG08', 'Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG09', 'It lays curses by thinking wicked thoughts. Writings tell that this Pokémon was born out of the assembly of five score and eight malevolent spirits.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG10', 'This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granaries—such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG11', 'Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform''s disposition!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh11tg-TG24', 'Lysandre')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-1', 'For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-2', 'It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-3', 'In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-4', 'Its two sharp scythes are more than just weapons. It uses them with dexterity to dress its prey before eating.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-5', 'It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-6', 'It roams through forests searching for sweet nectar. Although it boasts fantastic physical strength, it''s not that good at flying.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-7', 'It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-8', 'It is nocturnal and becomes active at nightfall. It feeds on aquatic mosses that grow in the riverbed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-9', 'The rhythm of bright, festive music activates Ludicolo''s cells, making it more powerful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-10', 'It lives in ponds and marshes that feature lots of plant life. It often fights with Dewpider, whose habitat and diet are similar.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-11', 'Its thin, winglike antennae are highly absorbent. It waits out rainy days in tree hollows.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-12', 'It lives on snowy mountains. It sinks its legs into the snow to absorb water and keep its own temperature down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-13', 'If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-14', 'After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit''s rebirth as this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-15', 'People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokémon it shares its woods with, it''s kind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-16', 'Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-20', 'It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it''s just an apple and nothing more.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-21', 'It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it''s just an apple and nothing more.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-22', 'It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-23', 'Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-24', 'While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-25', 'It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-27', 'It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-28', 'The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-29', 'Its entire body is burning. When it breathes, the temperature rises. When it sneezes, flames shoot out!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-30', 'Magmortar takes down its enemies by shooting fireballs, which burn them to a blackened crisp. It avoids this method when hunting prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-31', 'The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokémon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-32', 'This Pokémon appears just before someone passes away, so it''s feared as an emissary of death.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-33', 'This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-34', 'There''s a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-37', 'Its talent is tap-dancing. It can also manipulate temperatures to create a floor of ice, which this Pokémon can kick up to use as a barrier.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-38', 'It''s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-39', 'It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokémon in the world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-40', 'It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-41', 'It makes its nest on sheer cliffs. Riding the sea breeze, it glides up into the expansive skies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-42', 'It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-44', 'Graceful ripples running across the water''s surface are a sure sign that Tympole are singing in high-pitched voices below.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-45', 'It weakens its prey with sound waves intense enough to cause headaches, then entangles them with its sticky tongue.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-46', 'The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-47', 'It lived in snowy areas for so long that its fire sac cooled off and atrophied. It now has an organ that generates cold instead.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-48', 'On days when blizzards blow through, it comes down to where people live. It stashes food in the snowball on its head, taking it home for later.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-51', 'It''s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it''s battling midfight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-52', 'If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It''s very proud of that jaw.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-53', 'This Pokémon has a jaw that''s as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda''s flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-54', 'It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-56', 'Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-57', 'It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-58', 'While it''s often blamed for power outages, the truth is the cause of outages is more often an error on the part of the electric company.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-59', 'A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-60', 'All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-61', 'Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-62', 'Luxray''s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it''s scouting for danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-63', 'When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon''s electric moves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-64', 'A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-65', 'While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-66', 'It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-68', 'It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-69', 'When this Pokémon sounds as if it''s strumming a guitar, it''s actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-73', 'As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It''s also generating electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-74', 'It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-75', 'A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-76', 'It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-77', 'They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-78', 'Watch your step when wandering areas oceans once covered. What looks like a stone could be this Pokémon, and it will curse you if you kick it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-79', 'Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon''s core spirit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-80', 'Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians'' emissaries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-81', 'If you build sand mounds when you''re playing, destroy them before you go home, or they may get possessed and become Sandygast.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-82', 'Once it has whipped up a sandstorm to halt its opponents in their tracks, this terrifying Pokémon snatches away their vitality.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-83', 'Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures'' emotions. If you don''t have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-84', 'No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-85', 'It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-86', 'This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-87', 'When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it''s decorated with cream.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-88', 'These intelligent Pokémon touch horns with each other to share information between them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-89', 'After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-90', 'It''s capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-91', 'When it isn''t battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-94', 'The Farfetch''d of the Galar region are brave warriors, and they wield thick, tough leeks in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-95', 'Only Farfetch''d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon''s leek withers, it will retire from combat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-96', 'It hunts without twitching a muscle by pulling in its prey with powerful magnetism. But sometimes it pulls natural enemies in close.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-97', 'It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-98', 'Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe''s next move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-99', 'Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-100', 'It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything—if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-101', 'A clay slab with cursed engravings took possession of a Yamask. The slab is said to be absorbing the Yamask''s dark power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-102', 'A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-103', 'After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-104', 'Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-105', 'Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-106', 'It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-107', 'It''s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-109', 'Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass''s orders are absolute.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-111', 'It stands in grasslands, watching the sun''s descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-112', 'Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-113', 'This Pokémon consumes particles that contaminate the air. Instead of leaving droppings, it expels clean air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-114', 'From its rear, it sprays a foul-smelling liquid at opponents. It aims for their faces, and it can hit them from over 16 feet away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-115', 'In its belly, it reserves stinky fluid that it shoots from its tail during battle. As this Pokémon''s diet varies, so does the stench of its fluid.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-116', 'It was bound to a fissure in an Odd Keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-117', 'Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-118', 'This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-119', 'It wears a bone to protect its rear. It often squabbles with others of its kind over particularly comfy bones.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-120', 'Although it''s a bit of a ruffian, this Pokémon will take lost Vullaby under its wing and care for them till they''re ready to leave the nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-123', 'Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-124', 'When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it''s trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-125', 'With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-126', 'Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokémon''s body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-127', 'What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-128', 'Once it has identified something as an enemy, it will continue beating them with its steel-hard pincers until there''s nothing left but scraps.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-129', 'It appears in ancient ruins. The pattern on its body doesn''t come from any culture in the Galar region, so it remains shrouded in mystery.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-130', 'Some believe it to be a deity that summons rain clouds. When angered, it lets out a warning cry that rings out like the tolling of a bell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-131', 'It uses three small units to catch prey and battle enemies. The main body mostly just gives orders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-132', 'They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor, they retaliate using their massive mandibles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-133', 'Honedge''s soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge''s body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-134', 'Honedge evolves into twins. The two blades rub together to emit a metallic sound that unnerves opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-135', 'In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-138', 'Its body resembles polished metal, and it''s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-139', 'Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-140', 'Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master''s Shield. It was feared and respected by all.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-141', 'It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-142', 'It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-143', 'Where people go, these Pokémon follow. If you''re scattering food for them, be careful—several hundred of them can gather at once.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-144', 'It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels, it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-145', 'Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-146', 'It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-147', 'With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It''s a huge help during tunnel construction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-148', 'It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-149', 'Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-150', 'Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-151', 'Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-152', 'It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn''t notice the loss.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-204', 'It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh2-205', 'What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-3', 'The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-4', 'The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-5', 'It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-6', 'It''s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It''s kind enough to share them with friends.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-7', 'Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-8', 'Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-9', 'When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-10', 'It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-11', 'At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-12', 'It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-13', 'As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye''s shots never miss.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-14', 'Its body gives off a sweet, fruity scent that is extremely appetizing to bird Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-15', 'As it twirls like a dancer, a sweet smell spreads out around it. Anyone who inhales the scent will feel a surge of happiness.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-16', 'This feared Pokémon has long, slender legs and a cruel heart. It shows no mercy as it stomps on its opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-17', 'It''s nature''s cleaner—it eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-18', 'It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-22', 'A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-23', 'During a battle, the hot flame in its body increases. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-24', 'When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-25', 'Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-26', 'This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-27', 'When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-28', 'Anger has reignited its atrophied flame sac. This Pokémon spews fire everywhere as it rampages indiscriminately.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-29', 'It protects itself with flame. Long years ago, people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-30', 'According to legends, it was hatched from a flaming cocoon to save people and Pokémon that were suffering from the cold.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-31', 'Its speed right after takeoff already puts it in the top speed class of all bird Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-32', 'Bird Pokémon make up most of its diet. It approaches at high speeds and smacks them down to the ground with its powerful kick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-35', 'Its talent is tap-dancing. It can also manipulate temperatures to create a floor of ice, which this Pokémon can kick up to use as a barrier.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-36', 'It''s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-37', 'Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-38', 'Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokémon''s marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-39', 'Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-40', 'The reason it hasn''t changed at all in a hundred million years is that it''s apparently already a perfect life-form.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-41', 'The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-42', 'It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-43', 'It lived in snowy areas for so long that its fire sac cooled off and atrophied. It now has an organ that generates cold instead.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-44', 'On days when blizzards blow through, it comes down to where people live. It stashes food in the snowball on its head, taking it home for later.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-45', 'Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-46', 'By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body. This Pokémon can be hard to find on days with warm, sunny weather.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-47', 'When its anger reaches a breaking point, this Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it, be they friend or foe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-48', 'When this Pokémon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn''t like.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-49', 'It swims through frigid seas, searching for prey. From its frozen breath, it forms icy fangs that are harder than steel.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-50', 'Individually, they''re incredibly weak. It''s by gathering up into schools that they''re able to confront opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-51', 'The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it''s impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-52', 'To survive in the cold waters of Galar, this Pokémon forms a dome with its legs, enclosing its body so it can capture its own body heat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-53', 'Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-54', 'Though it''s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-55', 'Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You''ll want to pet it because it''s cute, but if you use your bare hand, you''ll get a painful shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-56', 'It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-57', 'Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-58', 'It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-59', 'It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-61', 'The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-62', 'It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-63', 'Capable of generating 15,000 volts of electricity, this Pokémon looks down on all that would challenge it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-64', 'It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-65', 'In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-66', 'The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-67', 'The songs they sing are totally different depending on the region they live in. Some even sound like they''re shouting!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-68', 'When it gets angry, it inhales with all its might, and its body gradually inflates. Sometimes they can grow 20 times larger!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-70', 'In contrast to its appearance, it''s quite timid. When playing with other puppy Pokémon, it sometimes gets bullied.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-71', 'Although it''s popular with young people, Granbull is timid and sensitive, so it''s totally incompetent as a watchdog.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-72', 'The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It''s active on the night of a full moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-73', 'Though they''re still only babies, there''s psychic power stored in their ribbonlike feelers, and sometimes they use that power to fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-74', 'It''s said that when stars shine in the night sky, this Pokémon will spirit away sleeping children. Some call it the Witch of Punishment.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-75', 'It has tremendous psychic power, but it dislikes conflict. It''s also able to predict the future based on the movement of the stars.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-76', 'They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-77', 'Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-78', 'Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-79', 'Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull''s head. The caps regrow overnight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-80', 'Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-81', 'It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-82', 'This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-83', 'This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-84', 'If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-85', 'A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-86', 'Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-87', 'Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-88', 'Its body can''t be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-89', 'Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-90', 'The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-91', 'This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-92', 'When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-93', 'It moves through the sands with its mouth open, swallowing sand along with its prey. It gets rid of the sand by spouting it from its nose.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-94', 'Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-96', 'With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It''s a huge help during tunnel construction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-97', 'Displaying amazing teamwork, they follow the orders of their boss as they all help out in the search for their favorite berries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-98', 'Only Farfetch''d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon''s leek withers, it will retire from combat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-100', 'The wastewater coming from factories is clean these days, so Grimer have nothing to eat. They''re said to be on the verge of extinction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-101', 'Because they scatter germs everywhere, they''ve long been targeted for extermination, leading to a steep decline in their population.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-102', 'Although the poison from its fangs isn''t that strong, it''s potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-103', 'It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-105', 'It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-106', 'It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-107', 'Don''t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-108', 'When it encounters something, its first urge is usually to bite it. If it likes what it tastes, it will commit the associated scent to memory.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-109', 'While hunting for prey, Zweilous wanders its territory, its two heads often bickering over which way to go.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-110', 'There are a slew of stories about villages that were destroyed by Hydreigon. It bites anything that moves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-111', 'It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-112', 'Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-113', 'It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-120', 'Its body is draped in steel armor. It looks heavy, but it can fly at speeds of up to 185 miles an hour!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-121', 'When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-122', 'It habitually shows off its strength with the sparks it creates by ramming its steel body into boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-123', 'While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-124', 'They use shells they''ve stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They''re very popular Pokémon in the Galar region.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-125', 'The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-126', 'When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon''s rotation speed increases sharply.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-127', 'From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-129', 'It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-130', 'At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-131', 'It digs up the ground with its trunk. It''s also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-132', 'They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-133', 'You shouldn''t get close to the child when it''s playing outside its mother''s pouch. Its mother is always nearby watching over it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-134', 'They live in groups. The one with the longest, thickest, and most-scarred horns is the boss of the herd.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-135', 'It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-136', 'It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-137', 'When it sees a person, it digs a hole with its tail to make its escape. If you happen to find one, consider yourself lucky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-138', 'Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-139', 'Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-140', 'It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-141', 'It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-142', 'It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-145', 'They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-146', 'It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-147', 'When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-148', 'They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-149', 'Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-150', 'It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-151', 'Its body is always warm. Trainers who live in cold areas apparently sleep with it in their bed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-152', 'Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-153', 'It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn''t notice the loss.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-154', 'It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-155', 'Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-156', 'This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-197', 'By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh3-198', 'It''s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-2', 'Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-3', 'While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-4', 'May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-6', 'While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-7', 'When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being''s entire body will be overflowing with power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-9', 'It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-10', 'When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-11', 'With its sturdy jaws and fangs, it can easily chomp wooden boats to splinters. It fights with Basculin over food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-12', 'It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to propel itself. It''s very sensitive to the scent of blood.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-18', 'Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures'' emotions. If you don''t have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-19', 'No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-20', 'It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-24', 'Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it''s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-25', 'Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-26', 'It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-28', 'Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-29', 'When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that''s proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-30', 'The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-31', 'Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-33', 'The eggs of bird Pokémon are its favorite food. It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg gets stuck, and Ekans faints.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-34', 'After stunning its opponents with the pattern on its stomach, it quickly wraps them up in its body and waits for them to stop moving.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-35', 'Its restlessness has it constantly running around. If it sees another Pokémon, it will purposely run into them in order to start a fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-36', 'It uses its long tongue to taunt opponents. Once the opposition is enraged, this Pokémon hurls itself at the opponent, tackling them forcefully.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-37', 'Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-38', 'The elderly call it the disaster Pokémon and detest it, but interest in its power to predict disasters is on the rise.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-39', 'It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-40', 'Don''t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-41', 'If it locks eyes with you, watch out! Nothing and no one is safe from the reckless headbutts of this troublesome Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-42', 'As halfhearted as this Pokémon''s kicks may seem, they pack enough power to shatter Conkeldurr''s concrete pillars.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-43', 'Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-44', 'It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-45', 'Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar''s control.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-46', 'Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-48', 'It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh35-49', 'On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-1', 'Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-2', 'While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-3', 'May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-4', 'Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-5', 'Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-6', 'If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-7', 'This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-8', 'It sticks tree bark to itself with its saliva, making itself thicker and larger. Elderly Pineco are ridiculously huge.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-9', 'This Pokémon has the ability to move through time. Records describing it as a forest deity can be found from many different eras.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-10', 'If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-11', 'It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-12', 'A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe''s mind and take preemptive action.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-13', 'Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-14', 'Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-15', 'The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-16', 'This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-17', 'If it has sunshine and water, it doesn''t need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-18', 'They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-19', 'After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-23', 'It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-24', 'It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-25', 'It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-26', 'Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokémon''s body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-27', 'Its body is made of magma. If it doesn''t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-28', 'Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-30', 'When Vaporeon''s fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-31', 'It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-32', 'It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-33', 'It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-34', 'As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-35', 'One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-38', 'Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-39', 'With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-40', 'Cramorant''s gluttony led it to try to swallow an Arrokuda whole, which in turn led to Cramorant getting an Arrokuda stuck in its throat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-41', 'If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It''s very proud of that jaw.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-42', 'This Pokémon has a jaw that''s as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda''s flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-45', 'Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-46', 'It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-47', 'If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-48', 'A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-50', 'This rough Pokémon stores energy inside its body, then sweeps across the land, shooting off electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-51', 'It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-52', 'It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-53', 'Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-54', 'They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-55', 'Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It''s soaking up static electricity because it can''t produce a charge on its own.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-56', 'It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-57', 'One alone can emit only trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-58', 'These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-59', 'They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-60', 'When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-61', 'It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-62', 'It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-63', 'It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-64', 'A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-65', 'Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-66', 'A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-67', 'There''s a proverb that says, "Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-68', 'Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-69', 'If it finds bad children who won''t listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it''s said.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-70', 'Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-71', 'At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-72', 'Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-73', 'While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it''s evidence that Woobat live there.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-74', 'Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won''t be able to fly for a little while.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-75', 'It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-76', 'It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it''ll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-77', 'Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-78', 'When the horns on its head shine in seven different colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-79', 'It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-80', 'This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-81', 'When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it''s decorated with cream.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-82', 'Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-83', 'This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-84', 'It has an easygoing nature. It doesn''t care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-85', 'It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-86', 'It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-87', 'The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-88', 'It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-89', 'The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-90', 'It''s exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-91', 'It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-92', 'It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-93', 'Born when all of Zygarde''s cells have been gathered together, it uses force to neutralize those who harm the ecosystem.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-94', 'When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that''s proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-95', 'They live alone without forming packs. They will only listen to orders from Trainers who can draw out their true power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-96', 'Loads weighing up to 50 times as much as its own body weight pose no issue for this Pokémon. It''s skilled at making use of mud.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-97', 'Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale''s legs sets harder than stone. It''s so hard that it allows this Pokémon to scrap a truck with a single kick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-100', 'It''s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-101', 'A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-102', 'Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master''s Shield. It was feared and respected by all.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-103', 'It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-104', 'It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-105', 'This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it''s believed that Sableye will steal people''s spirits away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-107', 'Sandile''s still not good at hunting, so it mostly eats things that have collapsed in the desert. It''s called "the cleaner of the desert."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-108', 'It buries some of its prey in the sand to use as emergency meals when its hunts are unsuccessful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-109', 'It conceals itself in sandstorms that Flygon whip up and waits patiently for prey to appear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-110', 'Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-111', 'This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-112', 'Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokémon''s body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-113', 'What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-114', 'In the moment that it gulps down its prey, the inside of its shell is exposed, but to this day, no one has ever seen that sight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-116', 'If you anger it, it will do more than rampage. It will also burst out strong magnetism, causing nearby machines to break.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-117', 'It flies at high speeds around the skies. When it finds its prey, Metang takes a firm grip with its sharp claws and never lets go.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-118', 'It analyzes its opponents with more accuracy than a supercomputer, which enables it to calmly back them into a corner.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-119', 'Once every 1,000 years, the singing of a pure voice will rouse this Pokémon from its near-perpetual slumber. It wakes for only seven days.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-120', 'It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-121', 'It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-122', 'It''s not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill''s rampant digging.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-123', 'It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn''t very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-124', 'This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-125', 'Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-128', 'Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-129', 'Its body resembles polished metal, and it''s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-130', 'It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-131', 'It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-132', 'It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-133', 'It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 180 miles a day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-134', 'It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-135', 'If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-136', 'The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-137', 'Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor—or like an earthquake has struck.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-138', 'It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-139', 'It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-142', 'Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-143', 'It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-144', 'From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-145', 'Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokémon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-198', 'It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh4-199', 'It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-1', 'If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-2', 'This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-3', 'It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-4', 'It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-5', 'Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-6', 'At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-7', 'It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-8', 'As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye''s shots never miss.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-11', 'When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-12', 'The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-13', 'By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-14', 'It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-15', 'The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-16', 'Once the vines on Zarude''s body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-17', 'When Reshiram''s tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world''s weather.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-20', 'It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-21', 'It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-22', 'It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-23', 'Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-24', 'It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-25', 'It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-26', 'It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-27', 'This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-28', 'This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-29', 'It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-30', 'It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-31', 'All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-32', 'Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-33', 'Luxray''s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it''s scouting for danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-34', 'One boy''s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom''s unique capabilities.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-35', 'As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It''s also generating electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-36', 'As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It''s also generating electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-40', 'Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-41', 'Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-42', 'This Pokémon consumes particles that contaminate the air. Instead of leaving droppings, it expels clean air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-43', 'Although the poison from its fangs isn''t that strong, it''s potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-46', 'When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-47', 'Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-48', 'It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-49', 'It digs up the ground with its trunk. It''s also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-52', 'It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45-56', 'It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV001', 'At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV002', 'It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV003', 'As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye''s shots never miss.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV004', 'When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV005', 'The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV006', 'By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV007', 'Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV008', 'As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV009', 'It emits psychic energy to observe and study what''s around it—and what''s around it can include things over six miles away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV010', 'It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV011', 'The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV012', 'It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it''s just an apple and nothing more.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV013', 'It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV014', 'Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV015', 'It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it''s raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV016', 'It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV017', 'It''s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV018', 'It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV019', 'When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV020', 'Its talent is tap-dancing. It can also manipulate temperatures to create a floor of ice, which this Pokémon can kick up to use as a barrier.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV021', 'It''s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV022', 'Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV023', 'It lived in snowy areas for so long that its fire sac cooled off and atrophied. It now has an organ that generates cold instead.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV024', 'On days when blizzards blow through, it comes down to where people live. It stashes food in the snowball on its head, taking it home for later.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV025', 'When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won''t be able to resist weeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV026', 'A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV027', 'It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV028', 'It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV029', 'This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV030', 'It''s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it''s battling midfight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV031', 'If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It''s very proud of that jaw.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV032', 'This Pokémon has a jaw that''s as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda''s flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV033', 'It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV034', 'It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV035', 'It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV036', 'Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV037', 'Though it''s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV038', 'One boy''s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom''s unique capabilities.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV039', 'This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV040', 'This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV041', 'It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV042', 'When this Pokémon sounds as if it''s strumming a guitar, it''s actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV043', 'It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV044', 'As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It''s also generating electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV045', 'In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV046', 'The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV047', 'This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV048', 'Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV049', 'Watch your step when wandering areas oceans once covered. What looks like a stone could be this Pokémon, and it will curse you if you kick it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV050', 'Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon''s core spirit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV051', 'Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV052', 'This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV053', 'This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV054', 'Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures'' emotions. If you don''t have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV055', 'No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV056', 'It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV057', 'This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV058', 'When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it''s decorated with cream.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV059', 'These intelligent Pokémon touch horns with each other to share information between them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV060', 'After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV061', 'It''s capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV062', 'When it isn''t battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV063', 'The Farfetch''d of the Galar region are brave warriors, and they wield thick, tough leeks in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV064', 'Only Farfetch''d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon''s leek withers, it will retire from combat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV065', 'A clay slab with cursed engravings took possession of a Yamask. The slab is said to be absorbing the Yamask''s dark power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV066', 'A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV067', 'Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV068', 'It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV069', 'It''s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV070', 'It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV071', 'Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV072', 'It''s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV073', 'A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV074', 'Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass''s orders are absolute.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV075', 'It stands in grasslands, watching the sun''s descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV076', 'Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV077', 'This Pokémon consumes particles that contaminate the air. Instead of leaving droppings, it expels clean air.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV078', 'Thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon, it moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV079', 'This very aggressive Pokémon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV080', 'It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV081', 'Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV082', 'It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV083', 'Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV084', 'When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it''s trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV085', 'With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV086', 'Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokémon''s body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV087', 'What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV088', 'Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV089', 'This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV090', 'It digs up the ground with its trunk. It''s also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV091', 'They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV092', 'Its body resembles polished metal, and it''s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV093', 'The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV094', 'Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won''t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV095', 'They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV096', 'Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV097', 'It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV098', 'It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV099', 'Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV100', 'It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn''t notice the loss.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV101', 'It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV102', 'Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV103', 'If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won''t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh45sv-SV104', 'Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-1', 'Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-2', 'It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-3', 'Once ingested into this Pokémon''s body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-4', 'It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-5', 'Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-7', 'The deeper a Cherubi''s red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-8', 'The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-9', 'It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-10', 'With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-11', 'The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-12', 'The beaks of birds can''t begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-13', 'The patterns on this Pokémon''s wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-14', 'It loves the sunshine. When it basks in the sunlight regularly, it grows up with vivid coloration.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-15', 'As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it''s dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-16', 'Although it''s called a guardian deity, it''s violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-17', 'Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-20', 'It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-23', 'It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-24', 'When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-25', 'It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-26', 'A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-27', 'This sneaky Pokémon will slink behind its prey and immobilize it with poisonous gas before the prey even realizes Salandit is there.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-28', 'The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-29', 'It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they''re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-30', 'While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-31', 'It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-32', 'It is capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its winglike pectoral fins and stout tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-33', 'It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life forms can survive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-34', 'It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It''ll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-35', 'Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-36', 'Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine''s underside to scavenge for leftovers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-37', 'It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-38', 'It was originally a Pokémon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-39', 'A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-41', 'Legend has it that the residents of a sunken ancient city changed into these Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-42', 'Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-43', 'Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie''s spikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunches up the spikes and eats them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-44', 'While it''s often blamed for power outages, the truth is the cause of outages is more often an error on the part of the electric company.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-45', 'A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-46', 'All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-47', 'Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-48', 'Luxray''s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it''s scouting for danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-49', 'A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-52', 'This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-53', 'It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-54', 'Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-55', 'It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-56', 'It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-57', 'It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-58', 'It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-59', 'Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-60', 'There''s enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can''t be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-61', 'The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It''s when they''re protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-64', 'As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-65', 'It emits psychic energy to observe and study what''s around it—and what''s around it can include things over six miles away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-66', 'If one gets angry, all the others around it will get angry, so silence is a rare visitor in a troop of Mankey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-67', 'The blood vessels in its brain are sturdier than those of other Pokémon, so it can stay healthy despite its constant raging.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-68', 'It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-69', 'It wears its mother''s skull on its head, so no one knows what its bare face looks like. However, it''s clear that it''s always crying.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-70', 'They thump their bones rhythmically to communicate among themselves. There are nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-71', 'It flies straight at its target''s face then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-72', 'Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey… Then its elongated fangs do the rest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-73', 'Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-74', 'Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there''s skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-75', 'When going all out, this Pokémon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-76', 'They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-77', 'When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail, you''re in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-78', 'It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-79', 'By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-80', 'While it''s engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-81', 'It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-82', 'Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-83', 'The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-84', 'Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-89', 'Their skin is so thin that they''ll be burned if sunlight hits them. When it gets cold out, they gather together to warm one another''s bodies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-90', 'They can suck down over 10 ounces of blood in one go. They have been known to drink so much blood that they can no longer fly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-91', 'It feeds on the blood of living people and Pokémon. If it can''t drink any blood for even a short while, it becomes weak and unable to fly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-92', 'If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-93', 'It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow''s presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-94', 'Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-95', 'They make repeated eerie howls before dawn to call attention to their pack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-96', 'Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-98', 'Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-99', 'It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-100', 'It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-101', 'Polishing Bronzor to a shine makes its surface reflect the truth, according to common lore. Be that as it may, Bronzor hates being polished.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-102', 'Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-103', 'A pack of these Pokémon forms to serve a Bisharp boss. Each Pawniard trains diligently, dreaming of one day taking the lead.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-104', 'Violent conflicts erupt between Bisharp and Fraxure over places where sharpening stones can be found.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-105', 'The blue eye on the sword''s handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people''s lives away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-106', 'The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-107', 'Once upon a time, a king with an Aegislash reigned over the land. His Pokémon eventually drained him of life, and his kingdom fell with him.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-108', 'Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokémon to build a kingdom to its liking.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-111', 'Due to its short wings, it can''t fly long distances. It wanders about restlessly and pecks at bug Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-112', 'Carrying food through Fearow''s territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-113', 'It licks filth clean with its tongue. Whatever it licks always stinks afterward, so whether it''s really clean is…questionable.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-114', 'It uses its tongue much more skillfully than its hands or its feet. It can deftly pick up a single small bean with its tongue.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-115', 'When it''s happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-116', 'To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-118', 'Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-119', 'Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it''s angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-120', 'Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-178', 'It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh5-179', 'Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-1', 'Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-2', 'While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-3', 'May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-4', 'These very cowardly Pokémon join together and use Reflect to protect their nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-5', 'It flies through the night sky, sprinkling sparkly dust. According to some, if that dust sticks to you, good things will happen to you.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-6', 'It roams through forests searching for sweet nectar. Although it boasts fantastic physical strength, it''s not that good at flying.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-9', 'The berries that grow around its belly are like ice pops. Galarian Darumaka absolutely love these berries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-10', 'This Pokémon is known to bring blizzards. A shake of its massive body is enough to cause whiteout conditions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-11', 'The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon''s fur. People use it to mark the seasons.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-12', 'They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck''s horns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-13', 'When under attack, it secretes a sweet and delicious sweat. The scent only calls more enemies to it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-14', 'Any Corvisquire that pecks at this Pokémon will be greeted with a smack from its sepals followed by a sharp kick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-15', 'A kick from the hardened tips of this Pokémon''s legs leaves a wound in the opponent''s body and soul that will never heal.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-16', 'It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-17', 'When it''s drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won''t even notice that it''s already knocked out its opponent.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-18', 'The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-19', 'Once the vines on Zarude''s body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-22', 'Castform changes to this form when it basks in bright sunlight. When you touch its glowing skin, it feels all dried out!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-23', 'It protects itself with flame. Long years ago, people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-24', 'According to legends, it was hatched from a flaming cocoon to save people and Pokémon that were suffering from the cold.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-26', 'It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it''s raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-27', 'It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-28', 'It''s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-29', 'Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-30', 'It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-31', 'With its claws, it leaves behind signs for its friends to find. The number of distinct signs is said to be over 500.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-32', 'It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and Pokémon, so it''s always scrounging around for more food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-33', 'This is Castform''s form when pelted by rain. In an experiment where it was placed in a shower, this Pokémon didn''t change to this form.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-34', 'This is Castform''s form when caught in a hailstorm. Its whole body is chilled, and its skin is partially frozen!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-35', 'It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as −150 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-36', 'It spits out cold air of nearly −60 degrees Fahrenheit to freeze its quarry. It brings frozen prey back to its lair and neatly lines them up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-37', 'Its body is covered in fluffy fur. The fur keeps it from feeling cold while it is rolling on ice.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-38', 'Be it Spheal or a Poké Ball, it will spin any round object on its nose with the greatest of ease.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-39', 'It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-40', 'Although it''s called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-41', 'When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-42', 'Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-43', 'Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes'' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-44', 'This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in defeating foes by raining many blows down on them. Its strikes are nonstop, flowing like a river.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-47', 'Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You''ll want to pet it because it''s cute, but if you use your bare hand, you''ll get a painful shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-48', 'It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-49', 'Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-50', 'Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-51', 'They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-52', 'As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-54', 'Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-55', 'With its gas-like body, it can sneak into any place it desires. However, it can be blown away by wind.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-56', 'If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-57', 'It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-59', 'If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-60', 'It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-61', 'To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-62', 'There''s a proverb that says, "Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk."')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-63', 'Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-64', 'Those who sleep holding Cresselia''s feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-65', 'This Pokémon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago, and it still follows those orders to this day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-66', 'There''s a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn''t been proven.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-67', 'The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix''s fluffy fur. This Pokémon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-68', 'Slurpuff''s fur contains a lot of air, making it soft to the touch and lighter than it looks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-69', 'By exposing foes to the blinking of its luminescent spots, Inkay demoralizes them, and then it seizes the chance to flee.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-70', 'It''s said that Malamar''s hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-71', 'If this Pokémon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-72', 'Using the braids on its head, it pummels foes to get them to quiet down. One blow from those braids would knock out a professional boxer.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-73', 'If you''re too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Forest Witch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-76', 'It burrows through the ground at a shallow depth. It leaves raised earth in its wake, making it easy to spot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-77', 'These Diglett triplets dig over 60 miles below sea level. No one knows what it''s like underground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-78', 'The stalks of leeks are thicker and longer in the Galar region. Farfetch''d that adapted to these stalks took on a unique form.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-79', 'After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-81', 'Sharply attuned to others'' wishes for help, this Pokémon seeks out those in need and aids them in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-82', 'It''s said that this Pokémon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to a vengeful spirit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-83', 'Never touch its shadowlike body, or you''ll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-84', 'Crabrawler has been known to mistake Exeggutor for a coconut tree and climb it. The enraged Exeggutor shakes it off and stomps it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-85', 'Before it stops to think, it just starts pummeling. There are records of its turning back avalanches with a flurry of punches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-86', 'When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that''s proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-87', 'They live alone without forming packs. They will only listen to orders from Trainers who can draw out their true power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-88', 'Passimian live in groups of about 20, with each member performing an assigned role. Through cooperation, the group survives.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-91', 'Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn''t alarmed when that happens—it knows they''ll grow back. It''s about as smart as a three-year-old.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-92', 'Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-93', 'If Kubfu pulls the long white hair on its head, its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from the depths of its belly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-94', 'It adores polluted air. Some claim that Koffing used to be more plentiful in the Galar region than they are now.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-95', 'Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-96', 'Long ago, during a time when droves of factories fouled the air with pollution, Weezing changed into this form for some reason.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-98', 'While chanting strange spells, this Pokémon combines its internal toxins with what it''s eaten, creating strange potions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-101', 'The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-102', 'Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It''s Zangoose''s archrival.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-103', 'It was bound to a fissure in an Odd Keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-105', 'Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-106', 'It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-107', 'With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-108', 'Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-109', 'When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-110', 'It habitually shows off its strength with the size of sparks it creates by ramming its steel body into boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-111', 'While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-114', 'It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-115', 'They live in groups. The one with the longest, thickest, and most-scarred horns is the boss of the herd.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-116', 'It was built 20 years ago by scientists who dreamed of exploring space. Their dreams have yet to come true.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-117', 'Even though it doesn''t die in the vacuum of space, it can''t move around very well in zero gravity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-118', 'A faulty update was added to its programming. Its behavior is noticeably strange, so the experiment may have been a failure.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-120', 'Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-121', 'Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform''s disposition!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-122', 'Its color changes for concealment and also when its mood or health changes. The darker the color, the healthier it is.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-123', 'The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-126', 'Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-127', 'It eats berries nonstop—a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It''ll show up on farms, searching for yet more berries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-128', 'Common throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-222', 'It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-223', 'Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh6-224', 'It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-1', 'Although it’s tough, it can’t handle cold well. When night falls, it buries itself in leafage and sleeps.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-2', 'It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-3', 'It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-4', 'Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-5', 'It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-6', 'Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-9', 'They prefer clean water and soil. When the environment they live in turns bad, the whole bunch will up and move to a new area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-10', 'It’s well liked by other Pokémon because of its beauty. The flower on its head needs constant care, or it will soon wither and rot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-11', 'It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-12', 'Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They’re mighty enough to crack Rhyperior’s carapace.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-15', 'It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-16', 'The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-17', 'As soon as it’s born, it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source, but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-19', 'It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-20', 'When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-22', 'This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-23', 'The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn’t use it on its prey. This Pokémon prefers to eat raw meat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-24', 'It has been found that its brain cells are 10 times more active when Psyduck is experiencing a headache.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-25', 'A professional swimmer, it can continue swimming for two days straight by waving its long tail skillfully.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-26', 'Its body is 99% water. The remaining 1% contains the organ that makes its poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-27', 'It communicates with others of its kind by lighting up the red orbs on its head. When the orbs are blinking, it’s a warning sign.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-32', 'Its leaf grew too large for it to live on land. That is how it began to live floating in the water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-33', 'It lives at the water’s edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-34', 'If it hears festive music, it begins moving in rhythm in order to amplify its power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-35', 'With its sturdy jaws and fangs, it can easily chomp wooden boats to splinters. It fights with Basculin over food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-36', 'It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to propel itself. It’s very sensitive to the scent of blood.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-37', 'It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-38', 'It’s said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you’re feeling.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-39', 'Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola’s branches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-42', 'It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can’t hear its cries of warning.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-43', 'They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-44', 'This Pokémon lives in areas of frigid cold. It secures itself to the back of an Avalugg by freezing its feet in place.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-45', 'As Avalugg moves about during the day, the cracks in its body deepen. The Pokémon’s body returns to a pristine state overnight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-46', 'When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-47', 'This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-49', 'When Pikachu meet, they’ll touch their tails together and exchange electricity through them as a form of greeting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-50', 'If its electric pouches run empty, it raises its tail to gather electricity from the atmosphere.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-52', 'On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-53', 'This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-54', 'Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You’ll want to pet it because it’s cute, but if you use your bare hand, you’ll get a painful shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-55', 'It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-56', 'Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-57', 'As it flies, it scatters electricity around, so bird Pokémon keep their distance. That’s why Emolga can keep all its food to itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-60', 'Its entire body is made up of a single organ that generates electrical energy. Regieleki is capable of creating all Galar’s electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-61', 'It puts its prey to sleep and devours their dreams. It seems that bad dreams taste sour, so Drowzee doesn’t particularly like eating them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-62', 'There are some Hypno that assist doctors with patients who can’t sleep at night in hospitals.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-63', 'Known as Articuno, this Pokémon fires beams that can immobilize opponents as if they had been frozen solid.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-66', 'To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-67', 'It feeds on gemstone crystals. In darkness, its eyes sparkle with the glitter of jewels.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-68', 'It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-69', 'The auspicious shape of this Pokémon’s nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-71', 'Flabébé wears a crown made from pollen it’s collected from its flower. The crown has hidden healing properties.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-72', 'It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-73', 'Its life can span several hundred years. It’s said to devote its entire life to protecting gardens.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-76', 'The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokémon that see it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-77', 'In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-78', 'An opponent’s aura can tell Cutiefly what that opponent’s next move will be. Then Cutiefly can glide around the attack and strike back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-79', 'Ribombee absolutely hate getting wet or rained on. In the cloudy Galar region, they are very seldom seen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-80', 'It sinks into the shadows of people and Pokémon, where it can understand their feelings and copy their capabilities.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-81', 'Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-82', 'One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-84', 'This Pokémon is active during the day and passes the cold desert nights burrowed snugly into the sand.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-85', 'When roused to violence by its rage, it spews out the quantities of sand it has swallowed and whips up a sandstorm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-86', 'When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-87', 'It relies on sound in order to monitor what’s in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it’s facing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-88', 'Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation— they can only be fired when the sun is out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-89', 'On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-90', 'This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-93', 'The sinister aura that blazes like molten fire around this Pokémon is what inspired the name Moltres.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-96', 'They live in holes bored in large trees. The sound of Nuzleaf’s grass flute fills listeners with dread.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-97', 'It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-98', 'It protects itself with its durable skin. It’s thought that this Pokémon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-99', 'While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-102', 'If a normally talkative child suddenly stops talking, it may have been replaced by Zorua.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-103', 'If it thinks humans are going to discover its den, Zoroark shows them visions that make them wander around in the woods.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-104', 'Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-105', 'With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-106', 'On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-107', 'Some theories suggest that its behavior of forcefully bashing its head into things stimulates cells that affect its evolution.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-108', 'Shelgon lives deep within caves. It stays shut up in its hard shell, dreaming of the day it will be able to fly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-109', 'Thanks to its fervent wishes, the cells in its body finally mutated, and at last it has its heart’s desire—wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-112', 'It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-113', 'Because it can’t see, this Pokémon is constantly biting at everything it touches, trying to keep track of its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-114', 'Their two heads will fight each other over a single piece of food. Zweilous are covered in scars even without battling others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-115', 'The three heads take turns sinking their teeth into the opponent. Their attacks won’t slow until their target goes down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-116', 'It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-118', 'Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-119', 'Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it’s angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-120', 'It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-121', 'Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-124', 'Its body is composed of crystallized dragon energy. Regidrago is said to have the powers of every dragon Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-125', 'Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-126', 'Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-127', 'Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-128', 'It draws symbols with the fluid that oozes from the tip of its tail. Depending on the symbol, Smeargle fanatics will pay big money for them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-129', 'If it eats just three leaves in a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20 hours a day.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-130', 'Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-131', 'It is the world’s most slothful Pokémon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-132', 'It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-133', 'This Pokémon is popular with beginners because it’s intelligent, obedient to its Trainer’s commands, and easy to raise.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-134', 'It has been living with people for so long that portrayals of it can be found on the walls of caves from long, long ago.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-135', 'Its fur is long and thick. A long time ago in cold regions, every household kept a Stoutland.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-136', 'A combative Pokémon, it’s ready to pick a fight with anyone. It has talons that can crush hard berries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-137', 'Because this Pokémon is hotheaded and belligerent, it’s Corviknight that’s taken the role of transportation in Galar.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-138', 'Its body is always warm. Trainers who live in cold areas apparently sleep with it in their bed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-139', 'Its speed right after takeoff already puts it in the top speed class of all bird Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh7-140', 'Bird Pokémon make up most of its diet. It approaches at high speeds and smacks them down to the ground with its powerful kick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-1', 'Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-2', 'Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can’t withstand a harsh attack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-3', 'It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-4', 'It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-5', 'It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-7', 'It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-8', 'Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-9', 'Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-10', 'It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-11', 'It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-12', 'Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They’re jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-13', 'It has a strange physiology that responds to electricity. When together with Karrablast, Shelmet evolves for some reason.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-14', 'Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-15', 'Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-16', 'With a voice like a human child’s, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-17', 'Small roots that extend from the tips of this Pokémon’s feet can tie into the trees of the forest and give Trevenant control over them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-18', 'It uses its big jaws to dig nests into the forest floor, and it loves to feed on sweet tree sap.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-19', 'Dewpider normally lives underwater. When it comes onto land in search of food, it takes water with it in the form of a bubble on its head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-20', 'It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-24', 'It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-25', 'The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-27', 'Once the vines on Zarude’s body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-28', 'As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-29', 'As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-30', 'Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-31', 'Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-32', 'Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-33', 'A Pokémon that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-34', 'Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-35', 'Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-36', 'When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-37', 'This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-38', 'When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-41', 'A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-42', 'This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-46', 'It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-47', 'It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-48', 'While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-49', 'While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-50', 'Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-51', 'Once it slams its shell shut, it is impossible to open, even by those with superior strength.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-52', 'No number of injuries can bother Staryu. Its amazing regenerative powers return it to its previous state in half a day!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-53', 'It rotates its geometrically shaped body to swim through the water. It always seems to be sending out mysterious radio waves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-54', 'Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-55', 'Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-56', 'Once it bites down, it won’t let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-57', 'When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-58', 'Even after Marill swims in a cold sea, its water- repellent fur dries almost as soon as Marill leaves the water. That’s why this Pokémon is never cold.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-59', 'The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it’s in the water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-60', 'The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-61', 'As it majestically swims, it doesn’t care if Remoraid attach to it to scavenge for its leftovers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-62', 'To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-63', 'Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has made its legs sturdy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-64', 'It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-65', 'Clamperl’s pearls are exceedingly precious. They can be more than 10 times as costly as Shellder’s pearls.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-66', 'Deep seas are their habitat. According to tradition, when Huntail wash up onshore, something unfortunate will happen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-67', 'It sucks bodily fluids out of its prey. The leftover meat sinks to the seafloor, where it becomes food for other Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-68', 'The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-69', 'It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-70', 'Known for their violence, these Pokémon have the most fights with schools of red-striped Basculin.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-71', 'The colder they get, the more energetic they are. They freeze their breath to make snowballs, using them as ammo for playful snowball fights.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-72', 'Though it has a gentle disposition, it''s also very strong. It will quickly freeze the snowball on its head before going for a headbutt.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-74', 'It moves around by jetting water from its right pincer. It has a poor sense of balance, so it’s terrible at swimming straight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-75', 'Its right arm is packed with meat. When its pincer falls off, it’s exported to be used as a cooking ingredient.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-77', 'It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-80', 'It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-81', 'This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-82', 'After it’s eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That’s when Cramorant swallows it up.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-83', 'It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-84', 'It eats snow that piles up on the ground. The more snow it eats, the bigger and more impressive the spikes on its back grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-85', 'It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-87', 'Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-88', 'It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-89', 'It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-90', 'It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-91', 'All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-92', 'Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-93', 'Luxray’s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it’s scouting for danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-94', 'With a body made of plasma, it can inhabit all sorts of machines. It loves to surprise others.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-95', 'One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-96', 'These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-97', 'They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-98', 'The sun powers this Pokémon’s electricity generation. Interruption of that process stresses Helioptile to the point of weakness.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-99', 'One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-100', 'Its digestive processes convert the leaves it eats into electricity. An electric sac in its belly stores the electricity for later use.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-101', 'If it carries a Charjabug to use as a spare battery, a flying Vikavolt can rapidly fire high-powered beams of electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-102', 'It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-105', 'It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-106', 'It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-107', 'This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-108', 'It has an electrical organ on its chest. While generating electricity, it fills its surroundings with sounds like the strumming of a bass guitar.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-109', 'It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they’re precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-110', 'The songs they sing are totally different depending on the region they live in. Some even sound like they’re shouting!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-111', 'When it gets angry, it inhales with all its might, and its body gradually inflates. Sometimes they can grow 20 times larger!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-112', 'Its strange cries sound like human language. There are some musicians who compose songs for Jynx to sing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-115', 'In contrast to its appearance, it’s quite timid. When playing with other puppy Pokémon, it sometimes gets bullied.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-116', 'Although it’s popular with young people, Granbull is timid and sensitive, so it’s totally incompetent as a watchdog.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-117', 'Sudden climate change wiped out this ancient kind of Corsola. This Pokémon absorbs others'' life-force through its branches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-118', 'Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You’ll become stiff as stone if you touch it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-119', 'It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-120', 'DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-121', 'It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it’s eating a good dream, and black when it’s eating a nightmare.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-122', 'It drowses and dreams all the time. It’s best to leave it be if it’s just woken up, as it’s a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-123', 'A discovery was made in the desert where Sigilyph fly. The ruins of what may have been an ancient city were found beneath the sands.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-124', 'Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-125', 'If you build sand mounds when you’re playing, destroy them before you go home, or they may get possessed and become Sandygast.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-126', 'Once it has whipped up a sandstorm to halt its opponents in their tracks, this terrifying Pokémon snatches away their vitality.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-127', 'They diligently serve people and Pokémon so they can gather feelings of gratitude. The females are particularly good at babysitting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-128', 'If this weak Pokémon is by itself, a mere child could defeat it. But if Dreepy has friends to help it train, it can evolve and become much stronger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-129', 'Without a Dreepy to place on its head and care for, it gets so uneasy it’ll try to substitute any Pokémon it finds for the missing Dreepy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-130', 'Apparently the Dreepy inside Dragapult’s horns eagerly look forward to being launched out at Mach speeds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-131', 'When its skin gets wrinkled from moisture, it heads for a volcano. It lies flat on a spot with a lot of geothermal heat and dries itself out.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-132', 'Thanks to its thick claws, it’s good at climbing trees. There are plenty of Sandslash that park themselves in trees and go right to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-133', 'If one gets angry, all the others around it will get angry, so silence is a rare visitor in a troop of Mankey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-134', 'The blood vessels in its brain are sturdier than those of other Pokémon, so it can stay healthy despite its constant raging.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-135', 'It uses both hands to climb precipitous cliffs. People who see it in action have been known to take up bouldering.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-136', 'It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-137', 'It detonates its own body. The power from that explosion can propel it up steep mountain paths with amazing speed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-138', 'It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-139', 'It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-140', 'It flies straight at its target’s face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-141', 'Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-142', 'There’s a rumor of a traditional recipe for stew that Trainers can use to raise strong Makuhita.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-143', 'Hariyama that are big and fat aren’t necessarily strong. There are some small ones that move nimbly and use moves skillfully.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-144', 'It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-145', 'It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-147', 'It’s a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-148', 'From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-149', 'Wanting to make sure it’s taken seriously, Pancham’s always giving others a glare. But if it’s not focusing, it ends up smiling.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-150', 'The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight, but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-151', 'The moves it uses to take down its prey would make a martial artist jealous. It tucks subdued prey under its arms to carry them to its nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-152', 'Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn’t alarmed when that happens—it knows they’ll grow back. It’s about as smart as a three-year-old.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-153', 'Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-154', 'The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-155', 'The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-159', 'Thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon, it moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-160', 'This very aggressive Pokémon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-161', 'It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-162', 'With its sturdy jaws and fangs, it can easily chomp wooden boats to splinters. It fights with Basculin over food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-163', 'It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to propel itself. It’s very sensitive to the scent of blood.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-164', 'The elderly call it the disaster Pokémon and detest it, but interest in its power to predict disasters is on the rise.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-165', 'Once diluted, its poison becomes medicinal. This Pokémon came into popularity after a pharmaceutical company chose it as a mascot.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-166', 'It booms out a victory croak when its prey goes down in defeat. This Pokémon and Seismitoad are related species.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-167', 'It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-168', 'This Pokémon was born from a bag stuffed with trash. Galarian Weezing relish the fumes belched by Trubbish.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-169', 'The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-170', 'If a normally talkative child suddenly stops talking, it may have been replaced by Zorua.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-171', 'If it thinks humans are going to discover its den, Zoroark shows them visions that make them wander around in the woods.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-172', 'Vullaby grow quickly. Bones that have gotten too small for older Vullaby to wear often get passed down to younger ones in the nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-173', 'They adorn themselves with bones. There seem to be fashion trends among them, as different bones come into and fall out of popularity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-174', 'Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-175', 'When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-176', 'It sneaks into people’s homes, stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-177', 'With sly cunning, it tries to lure people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-178', 'Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-179', 'Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-180', 'These daring Pokémon have coins on their foreheads. Darker coins are harder, and harder coins garner more respect among Meowth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-181', 'After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-182', 'Its body is draped in steel armor. It looks heavy, but it can fly at speeds of up to 185 miles an hour!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-183', 'Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-184', 'With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-186', 'Long ago it lived in mines, but once the minerals that make up its diet became scarcer, Klefki began appearing in human settlements.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-187', 'When it’s in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-188', 'It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-189', 'Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-190', 'With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region’s airborne taxi service.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-191', 'If a job requires serious strength, this Pokémon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning a vibrant green color.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-192', 'These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-193', 'It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-194', 'It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-195', 'Their horns are powerful sensors. As soon as Goomy pick up any sign of enemies, they go into hiding. This is how they’ve survived.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-196', 'The lump on its back contains its tiny brain. It thinks only of food and escaping its enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-197', 'Its form of offense is forcefully stretching out its horns. The strikes land 100 times harder than any blow from a heavyweight boxer.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-198', 'Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-199', 'It washes its face regularly to keep the coin on its forehead spotless. It doesn’t get along with Galarian Meowth.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-200', 'Its elegant and refined behavior clashes with that of the barbaric Perrserker. The relationship between the two is one of mutual disdain.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-202', 'Because the eggs on their bellies have been overharvested by people in the past, the Chansey population remains very small.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-203', 'This Pokémon is overflowing with love. Only Chansey that share a strong bond with their Trainer can evolve, so people say.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-204', 'You shouldn’t get close to the child when it’s playing outside its mother’s pouch. Its mother is always nearby watching over it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-205', 'Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-206', 'This Pokémon’s stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-207', 'When it sees a person, it digs a hole with its tail to make its escape. If you happen to find one, consider yourself lucky.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-208', 'The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-209', 'It draws symbols with the fluid that oozes from the tip of its tail. Depending on the symbol, Smeargle fanatics will pay big money for them.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-210', 'It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-211', 'It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-212', 'The reason it keeps one ear rolled up is so it can launch a swift counterattack if it’s attacked by an enemy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-213', 'It’s notably wary and has a dislike of fighting, but at the same time, it can deliver powerful kicks with its lithe legs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-214', 'It’s very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight’s flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-215', 'The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-216', 'It always strikes a pose before going for its finishing move. Sometimes opponents take advantage of that time to counterattack.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-219', 'Jumping nimbly about, this small-bodied Pokémon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-220', 'The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent’s strength.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-221', 'If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won’t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-222', 'If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won’t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-223', 'Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh8-280', 'It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-1', 'Though it may look like it''s just a bunch of eggs, it''s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-2', 'Each of Exeggutor''s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don''t seem to be very interested in one another.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-3', 'It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-4', 'It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-5', 'Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-6', 'It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-7', 'It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-8', 'Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-9', 'If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-10', 'When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon''s body. The cloak is never shed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-11', 'It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-12', 'The deeper a Cherubi''s red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-15', 'Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-19', 'Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-20', 'When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-21', 'It''s one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-23', 'It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-24', 'The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-25', 'It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-26', 'It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-30', 'If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you''ll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-31', 'A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-32', 'No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-33', 'A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-34', 'It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-35', 'Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-36', 'It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-37', 'The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-38', 'It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-39', 'Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-41', 'It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-42', 'When this Pokémon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn''t like.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-43', 'It swims through frigid seas, searching for prey. From its frozen breath, it forms icy fangs that are harder than steel.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-44', 'The hair on its head connects to the surface of its brain. When this Pokémon has something on its mind, its hair chills the air around it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-46', 'Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-47', 'The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-49', 'This Pokémon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-50', 'By joining its tail with that of another Luxio, this Pokémon can receive some of the other Luxio''s electricity and power up its own electric blasts.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-51', 'Luxray can see through solid objects. It will instantly spot prey trying to hide behind walls, even if the walls are thick.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-52', 'A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-53', 'It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-54', 'A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-55', 'This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-56', 'A Pokémon created by recombining Mew''s genes. It''s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-58', 'It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-59', 'This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-60', 'If it finds bad children who won''t listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it''s said.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-61', 'Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-62', 'At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-63', 'Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-66', 'Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians'' emissaries.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-67', 'Since Dedenne can''t generate as much electricity on its own, it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-70', 'They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-71', 'When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-72', 'It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-73', 'It hunts without twitching a muscle by pulling in its prey with powerful magnetism. But sometimes it pulls natural enemies in close.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-74', 'Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-75', 'The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-76', 'This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-77', 'When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon''s body. The cloak is never shed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-78', 'It''s exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-79', 'It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-80', 'It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles, Throh''s belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer''s sweat.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-81', 'If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength, it''s best to quietly pass by.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-82', 'They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-83', 'Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-84', 'The wastewater coming from factories is clean these days, so Grimer have nothing to eat. They''re said to be on the verge of extinction.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-85', 'Because they scatter germs everywhere, they''ve long been targeted for extermination, leading to a steep decline in their population.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-86', 'Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-87', 'They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-89', 'Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokémon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-90', 'It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-91', 'Don''t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-92', 'Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-93', 'When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it''s trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-94', 'With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-98', 'When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon''s body. The cloak is never shed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-99', 'It uses three small units to catch prey and battle enemies. The main body mostly just gives orders.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-100', 'Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-101', 'They use shells they''ve stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They''re very popular Pokémon in the Galar region.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-102', 'The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-103', 'When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon''s rotation speed increases sharply.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-104', 'From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-107', 'Gible prefers to stay in narrow holes in the sides of caves heated by geothermal energy. This way, Gible can stay warm even during a blizzard.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-108', 'This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from a protrusion on either side of its head to probe pitch-dark caves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-109', 'Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane, hunting down as much prey as it can.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-110', 'These Pokémon nest in the ground and use their tusks to crush hard berries. Crushing berries is also how they test each other''s strength.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-111', 'After battle, this Pokémon carefully sharpens its tusks on river rocks. It needs to take care of its tusks—if one breaks, it will never grow back.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-113', 'Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-115', 'The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-116', 'Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform''s disposition!')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-117', 'They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-118', 'It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-119', 'When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-120', 'It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-121', 'It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-124', 'The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-125', 'Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won''t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-126', 'Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9-127', 'It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG01', 'Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokémon''s body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG02', 'When Vaporeon''s fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG03', 'It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG04', 'If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG05', 'When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG06', 'At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG07', 'Since Dedenne can''t generate as much electricity on its own, it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG08', 'When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG09', 'It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG10', 'Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG11', 'Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swsh9tg-TG12', 'It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH001', 'When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH002', 'A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon''s body. Once that happens, it''s ready to fight at full power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH003', 'When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won''t be able to resist weeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH006', 'By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH007', 'It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH008', 'What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH009', 'Its body secrets oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won''t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH010', 'It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH011', 'Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH012', 'As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It''s also generating electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH013', 'Its small horn hides a healing power. With a few rubs from this Pokémon''s horn, any slight wound you have will be healed.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH020', 'Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH022', 'It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH023', 'Luxray''s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it''s scouting for danger.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH024', 'It''s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH025', 'This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH026', 'If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH027', 'When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH028', 'Its body resembles polished metal, and it''s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH029', 'It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH031', 'As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It''s also generating electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH032', 'It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH033', 'Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH034', 'Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master''s Shield. It was feared and respected by all.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH035', 'As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye''s shots never miss.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH036', 'The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH037', 'There are a slew of stories about villages that were destroyed by Hydreigon. It bites anything that moves.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH038', 'You shouldn''t get close to the child when it''s playing outside its mother''s pouch. Its mother is always nearby watching over it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH039', 'Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH040', 'Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures'' emotions. If you don''t have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH041', 'Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokémon''s body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH042', 'It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH046', 'The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH047', 'This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH048', 'When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH051', 'A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH052', 'On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar''s doing.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH053', 'It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH054', 'It''s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH058', 'When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it''s decorated with cream.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH059', 'It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH060', 'Its body resembles polished metal, and it''s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH066', 'It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH067', 'The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH068', 'It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH069', 'It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH070', 'When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH071', 'A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon''s body. Once that happens, it''s ready to fight at full power.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH072', 'When Vaporeon''s fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH073', 'When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attacks won''t be able to resist weeping.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH074', 'Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH079', 'It''s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH080', 'Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH081', 'This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH082', 'It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH088', 'The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH089', 'It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH090', 'Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH091', 'Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.')
INSERT FLAVORTEXT VALUES ('swshp-SWSH092', 'It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.')
